7511  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_X : RISCVISD::FCVT_XU;
7512  else
7513  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64 : RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64;
7514 
7515  SDLoc DL(N);
7516  SDValue FpToInt = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, XLenVT, Src.getOperand(0),
7517  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, XLenVT));
7518  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, FpToInt);
7519 }
7520 
7521 // Fold
7522 // (fp_to_int_sat (froundeven X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rne))
7523 // (fp_to_int_sat (ftrunc X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rtz))
7524 // (fp_to_int_sat (ffloor X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rdn))
7525 // (fp_to_int_sat (fceil X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rup))
7526 // (fp_to_int_sat (fround X)) -> (select X == nan, 0, (fcvt X, rmm))
7527 static SDValue performFP_TO_INT_SATCombine(SDNode *N,
7528  TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
7529  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
7530  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
7531  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
7532  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7533 
7534  // Only handle XLen types. Other types narrower than XLen will eventually be
7535  // legalized to XLenVT.
7536  EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
7537  if (DstVT != XLenVT)
7538  return SDValue();
7539 
7540  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
7541 
7542  // Ensure the FP type is also legal.
7543  if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(Src.getValueType()))
7544  return SDValue();
7545 
7546  // Don't do this for f16 with Zfhmin and not Zfh.
7547  if (Src.getValueType() == MVT::f16 && !Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh())
7548  return SDValue();
7549 
7550  EVT SatVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT();
7551 
7552  RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode FRM = matchRoundingOp(Src);
7553  if (FRM == RISCVFPRndMode::Invalid)
7554  return SDValue();
7555 
7556  bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT;
7557 
7558  unsigned Opc;
7559  if (SatVT == DstVT)
7560  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_X : RISCVISD::FCVT_XU;
7561  else if (DstVT == MVT::i64 && SatVT == MVT::i32)
7562  Opc = IsSigned ? RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64 : RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64;
7563  else
7564  return SDValue();
7565  // FIXME: Support other SatVTs by clamping before or after the conversion.
7566 
7567  Src = Src.getOperand(0);
7568 
7569  SDLoc DL(N);
7570  SDValue FpToInt = DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, XLenVT, Src,
7571  DAG.getTargetConstant(FRM, DL, XLenVT));
7572 
7573  // RISCV FP-to-int conversions saturate to the destination register size, but
7574  // don't produce 0 for nan.
7575  SDValue ZeroInt = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, DstVT);
7576  return DAG.getSelectCC(DL, Src, Src, ZeroInt, FpToInt, ISD::CondCode::SETUO);
7577 }
7578 
7579 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
7580  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
7581  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
7582 
7583  // Helper to call SimplifyDemandedBits on an operand of N where only some low
7584  // bits are demanded. N will be added to the Worklist if it was not deleted.
7585  // Caller should return SDValue(N, 0) if this returns true.
7586  auto SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper = [&](unsigned OpNo, unsigned LowBits) {
7587  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(OpNo);
7588  APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(Op.getValueSizeInBits(), LowBits);
7589  if (!SimplifyDemandedBits(Op, Mask, DCI))
7590  return false;
7591 
7592  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE)
7593  DCI.AddToWorklist(N);
7594  return true;
7595  };
7596 
7597  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
7598  default:
7599  break;
7600  case RISCVISD::SplitF64: {
7601  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
7602  // If the input to SplitF64 is just BuildPairF64 then the operation is
7603  // redundant. Instead, use BuildPairF64's operands directly.
7604  if (Op0->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::BuildPairF64)
7605  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Op0.getOperand(0), Op0.getOperand(1));
7606 
7607  SDLoc DL(N);
7608 
7609  // It's cheaper to materialise two 32-bit integers than to load a double
7610  // from the constant pool and transfer it to integer registers through the
7611  // stack.
7612  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op0)) {
7613  APInt V = C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
7614  SDValue Lo = DAG.getConstant(V.trunc(32), DL, MVT::i32);
7615  SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(V.lshr(32).trunc(32), DL, MVT::i32);
7616  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, Hi);
7617  }
7618 
7619  // This is a target-specific version of a DAGCombine performed in
7620  // DAGCombiner::visitBITCAST. It performs the equivalent of:
7621  // fold (bitconvert (fneg x)) -> (xor (bitconvert x), signbit)
7622  // fold (bitconvert (fabs x)) -> (and (bitconvert x), (not signbit))
7623  if (!(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG || Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) ||
7624  !Op0.getNode()->hasOneUse())
7625  break;
7626  SDValue NewSplitF64 =
7627  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SplitF64, DL, DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32),
7628  Op0.getOperand(0));
7629  SDValue Lo = NewSplitF64.getValue(0);
7630  SDValue Hi = NewSplitF64.getValue(1);
7631  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignMask(32);
7632  if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG) {
7633  SDValue NewHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Hi,
7634  DAG.getConstant(SignBit, DL, MVT::i32));
7635  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, NewHi);
7636  }
7637  assert(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS);
7638  SDValue NewHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MVT::i32, Hi,
7639  DAG.getConstant(~SignBit, DL, MVT::i32));
7640  return DCI.CombineTo(N, Lo, NewHi);
7641  }
7642  case RISCVISD::SLLW:
7643  case RISCVISD::SRAW:
7644  case RISCVISD::SRLW:
7645  case RISCVISD::ROLW:
7646  case RISCVISD::RORW: {
7647  // Only the lower 32 bits of LHS and lower 5 bits of RHS are read.
7648  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32) ||
7649  SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, 5))
7650  return SDValue(N, 0);
7651  break;
7652  }
7653  case RISCVISD::CLZW:
7654  case RISCVISD::CTZW: {
7655  // Only the lower 32 bits of the first operand are read
7656  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32))
7657  return SDValue(N, 0);
7658  break;
7659  }
7660  case RISCVISD::GREV:
7661  case RISCVISD::GORC: {
7662  // Only the lower log2(Bitwidth) bits of the the shift amount are read.
7663  unsigned BitWidth = N->getOperand(1).getValueSizeInBits();
7664  assert(isPowerOf2_32(BitWidth) && "Unexpected bit width");
7665  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, Log2_32(BitWidth)))
7666  return SDValue(N, 0);
7667 
7668  return combineGREVI_GORCI(N, DAG);
7669  }
7670  case RISCVISD::GREVW:
7671  case RISCVISD::GORCW: {
7672  // Only the lower 32 bits of LHS and lower 5 bits of RHS are read.
7673  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32) ||
7674  SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, 5))
7675  return SDValue(N, 0);
7676 
7677  return combineGREVI_GORCI(N, DAG);
7678  }
7679  case RISCVISD::SHFL:
7680  case RISCVISD::UNSHFL: {
7681  // Only the lower log2(Bitwidth)-1 bits of the the shift amount are read.
7682  unsigned BitWidth = N->getOperand(1).getValueSizeInBits();
7683  assert(isPowerOf2_32(BitWidth) && "Unexpected bit width");
7684  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, Log2_32(BitWidth) - 1))
7685  return SDValue(N, 0);
7686 
7687  break;
7688  }
7689  case RISCVISD::SHFLW:
7690  case RISCVISD::UNSHFLW: {
7691  // Only the lower 32 bits of LHS and lower 4 bits of RHS are read.
7692  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
7693  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
7694  APInt LHSMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(LHS.getValueSizeInBits(), 32);
7695  APInt RHSMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(RHS.getValueSizeInBits(), 4);
7696  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32) ||
7697  SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, 4))
7698  return SDValue(N, 0);
7699 
7700  break;
7701  }
7702  case RISCVISD::BCOMPRESSW:
7703  case RISCVISD::BDECOMPRESSW: {
7704  // Only the lower 32 bits of LHS and RHS are read.
7705  if (SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(0, 32) ||
7706  SimplifyDemandedLowBitsHelper(1, 32))
7707  return SDValue(N, 0);
7708 
7709  break;
7710  }
7711  case RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH:
7712  case RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64: {
7713  SDLoc DL(N);
7714  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
7715  MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0);
7716  // If the input to FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64 is just FMV_W_X_RV64 then the
7717  // conversion is unnecessary and can be replaced with the FMV_W_X_RV64
7718  // operand. Similar for FMV_X_ANYEXTH and FMV_H_X.
7719  if ((N->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64 &&
7720  Op0->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_W_X_RV64) ||
7721  (N->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH &&
7722  Op0->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_H_X)) {
7723  assert(Op0.getOperand(0).getValueType() == VT &&
7724  "Unexpected value type!");
7725  return Op0.getOperand(0);
7726  }
7727 
7728  // This is a target-specific version of a DAGCombine performed in
7729  // DAGCombiner::visitBITCAST. It performs the equivalent of:
7730  // fold (bitconvert (fneg x)) -> (xor (bitconvert x), signbit)
7731  // fold (bitconvert (fabs x)) -> (and (bitconvert x), (not signbit))
7732  if (!(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG || Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) ||
7733  !Op0.getNode()->hasOneUse())
7734  break;
7735  SDValue NewFMV = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VT, Op0.getOperand(0));
7736  unsigned FPBits = N->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64 ? 32 : 16;
7737  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignMask(FPBits).sextOrSelf(VT.getSizeInBits());
7738  if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG)
7739  return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, VT, NewFMV,
7740  DAG.getConstant(SignBit, DL, VT));
7741 
7742  assert(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS);
7743  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, NewFMV,
7744  DAG.getConstant(~SignBit, DL, VT));
7745  }
7746  case ISD::ADD:
7747  return performADDCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
7748  case ISD::SUB:
7749  return performSUBCombine(N, DAG);
7750  case ISD::AND:
7751  return performANDCombine(N, DAG);
7752  case ISD::OR:
7753  return performORCombine(N, DAG, Subtarget);
7754  case ISD::XOR:
7755  return performXORCombine(N, DAG);
7756  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
7757  return performANY_EXTENDCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
7758  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
7759  // Fold (zero_extend (fp_to_uint X)) to prevent forming fcvt+zexti32 during
7760  // type legalization. This is safe because fp_to_uint produces poison if
7761  // it overflows.
7762  if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64 && Subtarget.is64Bit()) {
7763  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
7764  if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_UINT &&
7765  isTypeLegal(Src.getOperand(0).getValueType()))
7766  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64,
7767  Src.getOperand(0));
7768  if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT && Src.hasOneUse() &&
7769  isTypeLegal(Src.getOperand(1).getValueType())) {
7770  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i64, MVT::Other);
7771  SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT, SDLoc(N), VTs,
7772  Src.getOperand(0), Src.getOperand(1));
7773  DCI.CombineTo(N, Res);
7774  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(Src.getValue(1), Res.getValue(1));
7775  DCI.recursivelyDeleteUnusedNodes(Src.getNode());
7776  return SDValue(N, 0); // Return N so it doesn't get rechecked.
7777  }
7778  }
7779  return SDValue();
7780  case RISCVISD::SELECT_CC: {
7781  // Transform
7782  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
7783  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
7784  SDValue TrueV = N->getOperand(3);
7785  SDValue FalseV = N->getOperand(4);
7786 
7787  // If the True and False values are the same, we don't need a select_cc.
7788  if (TrueV == FalseV)
7789  return TrueV;
7790 
7791  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->get();
7792  if (!ISD::isIntEqualitySetCC(CCVal))
7793  break;
7794 
7795  // Fold (select_cc (setlt X, Y), 0, ne, trueV, falseV) ->
7796  // (select_cc X, Y, lt, trueV, falseV)
7797  // Sometimes the setcc is introduced after select_cc has been formed.
7798  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && isNullConstant(RHS) &&
7799  LHS.getOperand(0).getValueType() == Subtarget.getXLenVT()) {
7800  // If we're looking for eq 0 instead of ne 0, we need to invert the
7801  // condition.
7802  bool Invert = CCVal == ISD::SETEQ;
7803  CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))->get();
7804  if (Invert)
7805  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
7806 
7807  SDLoc DL(N);
7808  RHS = LHS.getOperand(1);
7809  LHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
7810  translateSetCCForBranch(DL, LHS, RHS, CCVal, DAG);
7811 
7812  SDValue TargetCC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
7813  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, DL, N->getValueType(0),
7814  {LHS, RHS, TargetCC, TrueV, FalseV});
7815  }
7816 
7817  // Fold (select_cc (xor X, Y), 0, eq/ne, trueV, falseV) ->
7818  // (select_cc X, Y, eq/ne, trueV, falseV)
7819  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR && isNullConstant(RHS))
7820  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
7821  {LHS.getOperand(0), LHS.getOperand(1),
7822  N->getOperand(2), TrueV, FalseV});
7823  // (select_cc X, 1, setne, trueV, falseV) ->
7824  // (select_cc X, 0, seteq, trueV, falseV) if we can prove X is 0/1.
7825  // This can occur when legalizing some floating point comparisons.
7826  APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(LHS.getValueSizeInBits(), 1);
7827  if (isOneConstant(RHS) && DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(LHS, Mask)) {
7828  SDLoc DL(N);
7829  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
7830  SDValue TargetCC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
7831  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, LHS.getValueType());
7832  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SELECT_CC, DL, N->getValueType(0),
7833  {LHS, RHS, TargetCC, TrueV, FalseV});
7834  }
7835 
7836  break;
7837  }
7838  case RISCVISD::BR_CC: {
7839  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(1);
7840  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(2);
7841  ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(3))->get();
7842  if (!ISD::isIntEqualitySetCC(CCVal))
7843  break;
7844 
7845  // Fold (br_cc (setlt X, Y), 0, ne, dest) ->
7846  // (br_cc X, Y, lt, dest)
7847  // Sometimes the setcc is introduced after br_cc has been formed.
7848  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && isNullConstant(RHS) &&
7849  LHS.getOperand(0).getValueType() == Subtarget.getXLenVT()) {
7850  // If we're looking for eq 0 instead of ne 0, we need to invert the
7851  // condition.
7852  bool Invert = CCVal == ISD::SETEQ;
7853  CCVal = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))->get();
7854  if (Invert)
7855  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
7856 
7857  SDLoc DL(N);
7858  RHS = LHS.getOperand(1);
7859  LHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
7860  translateSetCCForBranch(DL, LHS, RHS, CCVal, DAG);
7861 
7862  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BR_CC, DL, N->getValueType(0),
7863  N->getOperand(0), LHS, RHS, DAG.getCondCode(CCVal),
7864  N->getOperand(4));
7865  }
7866 
7867  // Fold (br_cc (xor X, Y), 0, eq/ne, dest) ->
7868  // (br_cc X, Y, eq/ne, trueV, falseV)
7869  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::XOR && isNullConstant(RHS))
7870  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BR_CC, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
7871  N->getOperand(0), LHS.getOperand(0), LHS.getOperand(1),
7872  N->getOperand(3), N->getOperand(4));
7873 
7874  // (br_cc X, 1, setne, br_cc) ->
7875  // (br_cc X, 0, seteq, br_cc) if we can prove X is 0/1.
7876  // This can occur when legalizing some floating point comparisons.
7877  APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(LHS.getValueSizeInBits(), 1);
7878  if (isOneConstant(RHS) && DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(LHS, Mask)) {
7879  SDLoc DL(N);
7880  CCVal = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCVal, LHS.getValueType());
7881  SDValue TargetCC = DAG.getCondCode(CCVal);
7882  RHS = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, LHS.getValueType());
7883  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BR_CC, DL, N->getValueType(0),
7884  N->getOperand(0), LHS, RHS, TargetCC,
7885  N->getOperand(4));
7886  }
7887  break;
7888  }
7889  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
7890  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
7891  return performFP_TO_INTCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
7892  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
7893  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
7894  return performFP_TO_INT_SATCombine(N, DCI, Subtarget);
7895  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: {
7896  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
7897  if (!VT.isVector())
7898  break;
7899  // There is a form of VFSGNJ which injects the negated sign of its second
7900  // operand. Try and bubble any FNEG up after the extend/round to produce
7901  // this optimized pattern. Avoid modifying cases where FP_ROUND and
7902  // TRUNC=1.
7903  SDValue In2 = N->getOperand(1);
7904  // Avoid cases where the extend/round has multiple uses, as duplicating
7905  // those is typically more expensive than removing a fneg.
7906  if (!In2.hasOneUse())
7907  break;
7908  if (In2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND &&
7909  (In2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_ROUND || In2.getConstantOperandVal(1) != 0))
7910  break;
7911  In2 = In2.getOperand(0);
7912  if (In2.getOpcode() != ISD::FNEG)
7913  break;
7914  SDLoc DL(N);
7915  SDValue NewFPExtRound = DAG.getFPExtendOrRound(In2.getOperand(0), DL, VT);
7916  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, DL, VT, N->getOperand(0),
7917  DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, DL, VT, NewFPExtRound));
7918  }
7919  case ISD::MGATHER:
7920  case ISD::MSCATTER:
7921  case ISD::VP_GATHER:
7922  case ISD::VP_SCATTER: {
7923  if (!DCI.isBeforeLegalize())
7924  break;
7925  SDValue Index, ScaleOp;
7926  bool IsIndexScaled = false;
7927  bool IsIndexSigned = false;
7928  if (const auto *VPGSN = dyn_cast<VPGatherScatterSDNode>(N)) {
7929  Index = VPGSN->getIndex();
7930  ScaleOp = VPGSN->getScale();
7931  IsIndexScaled = VPGSN->isIndexScaled();
7932  IsIndexSigned = VPGSN->isIndexSigned();
7933  } else {
7934  const auto *MGSN = cast<MaskedGatherScatterSDNode>(N);
7935  Index = MGSN->getIndex();
7936  ScaleOp = MGSN->getScale();
7937  IsIndexScaled = MGSN->isIndexScaled();
7938  IsIndexSigned = MGSN->isIndexSigned();
7939  }
7940  EVT IndexVT = Index.getValueType();
7941  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
7942  // RISCV indexed loads only support the "unsigned unscaled" addressing
7943  // mode, so anything else must be manually legalized.
7944  bool NeedsIdxLegalization =
7945  IsIndexScaled ||
7946  (IsIndexSigned && IndexVT.getVectorElementType().bitsLT(XLenVT));
7947  if (!NeedsIdxLegalization)
7948  break;
7949 
7950  SDLoc DL(N);
7951 
7952  // Any index legalization should first promote to XLenVT, so we don't lose
7953  // bits when scaling. This may create an illegal index type so we let
7954  // LLVM's legalization take care of the splitting.
7955  // FIXME: LLVM can't split VP_GATHER or VP_SCATTER yet.
7956  if (IndexVT.getVectorElementType().bitsLT(XLenVT)) {
7957  IndexVT = IndexVT.changeVectorElementType(XLenVT);
7958  Index = DAG.getNode(IsIndexSigned ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND,
7959  DL, IndexVT, Index);
7960  }
7961 
7962  unsigned Scale = cast<ConstantSDNode>(ScaleOp)->getZExtValue();
7963  if (IsIndexScaled && Scale != 1) {
7964  // Manually scale the indices by the element size.
7965  // TODO: Sanitize the scale operand here?
7966  // TODO: For VP nodes, should we use VP_SHL here?
7967  assert(isPowerOf2_32(Scale) && "Expecting power-of-two types");
7968  SDValue SplatScale = DAG.getConstant(Log2_32(Scale), DL, IndexVT);
7969  Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, IndexVT, Index, SplatScale);
7970  }
7971 
7972  ISD::MemIndexType NewIndexTy = ISD::UNSIGNED_UNSCALED;
7973  if (const auto *VPGN = dyn_cast<VPGatherSDNode>(N))
7974  return DAG.getGatherVP(N->getVTList(), VPGN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
7975  {VPGN->getChain(), VPGN->getBasePtr(), Index,
7976  VPGN->getScale(), VPGN->getMask(),
7977  VPGN->getVectorLength()},
7978  VPGN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy);
7979  if (const auto *VPSN = dyn_cast<VPScatterSDNode>(N))
7980  return DAG.getScatterVP(N->getVTList(), VPSN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
7981  {VPSN->getChain(), VPSN->getValue(),
7982  VPSN->getBasePtr(), Index, VPSN->getScale(),
7983  VPSN->getMask(), VPSN->getVectorLength()},
7984  VPSN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy);
7985  if (const auto *MGN = dyn_cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N))
7986  return DAG.getMaskedGather(
7987  N->getVTList(), MGN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
7988  {MGN->getChain(), MGN->getPassThru(), MGN->getMask(),
7989  MGN->getBasePtr(), Index, MGN->getScale()},
7990  MGN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy, MGN->getExtensionType());
7991  const auto *MSN = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N);
7992  return DAG.getMaskedScatter(
7993  N->getVTList(), MSN->getMemoryVT(), DL,
7994  {MSN->getChain(), MSN->getValue(), MSN->getMask(), MSN->getBasePtr(),
7995  Index, MSN->getScale()},
7996  MSN->getMemOperand(), NewIndexTy, MSN->isTruncatingStore());
7997  }
7998  case RISCVISD::SRA_VL:
7999  case RISCVISD::SRL_VL:
8000  case RISCVISD::SHL_VL: {
8001  SDValue ShAmt = N->getOperand(1);
8002  if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL) {
8003  // We don't need the upper 32 bits of a 64-bit element for a shift amount.
8004  SDLoc DL(N);
8005  SDValue VL = N->getOperand(3);
8006  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8007  ShAmt =
8008  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL, DL, VT, ShAmt.getOperand(0), VL);
8009  return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VT, N->getOperand(0), ShAmt,
8010  N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3));
8011  }
8012  break;
8013  }
8014  case ISD::SRA:
8015  case ISD::SRL:
8016  case ISD::SHL: {
8017  SDValue ShAmt = N->getOperand(1);
8018  if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL) {
8019  // We don't need the upper 32 bits of a 64-bit element for a shift amount.
8020  SDLoc DL(N);
8021  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8022  ShAmt =
8023  DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_I64, DL, VT, ShAmt.getOperand(0));
8024  return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VT, N->getOperand(0), ShAmt);
8025  }
8026  break;
8027  }
8028  case RISCVISD::MUL_VL:
8029  if (SDValue V = combineMUL_VLToVWMUL_VL(N, DAG, /*Commute*/ false))
8030  return V;
8031  // Mul is commutative.
8032  return combineMUL_VLToVWMUL_VL(N, DAG, /*Commute*/ true);
8033  case ISD::STORE: {
8034  auto *Store = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
8035  SDValue Val = Store->getValue();
8036  // Combine store of vmv.x.s to vse with VL of 1.
8037  // FIXME: Support FP.
8038  if (Val.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::VMV_X_S) {
8039  SDValue Src = Val.getOperand(0);
8040  EVT VecVT = Src.getValueType();
8041  EVT MemVT = Store->getMemoryVT();
8042  // The memory VT and the element type must match.
8043  if (VecVT.getVectorElementType() == MemVT) {
8044  SDLoc DL(N);
8045  MVT MaskVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
8046  return DAG.getStoreVP(
8047  Store->getChain(), DL, Src, Store->getBasePtr(), Store->getOffset(),
8048  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MaskVT),
8049  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, Subtarget.getXLenVT()), MemVT,
8050  Store->getMemOperand(), Store->getAddressingMode(),
8051  Store->isTruncatingStore(), /*IsCompress*/ false);
8052  }
8053  }
8054 
8055  break;
8056  }
8057  }
8058 
8059  return SDValue();
8060 }
8061 
8062 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isDesirableToCommuteWithShift(
8063  const SDNode *N, CombineLevel Level) const {
8064  // The following folds are only desirable if `(OP _, c1 << c2)` can be
8065  // materialised in fewer instructions than `(OP _, c1)`:
8066  //
8067  // (shl (add x, c1), c2) -> (add (shl x, c2), c1 << c2)
8068  // (shl (or x, c1), c2) -> (or (shl x, c2), c1 << c2)
8069  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
8070  EVT Ty = N0.getValueType();
8071  if (Ty.isScalarInteger() &&
8072  (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || N0.getOpcode() == ISD::OR)) {
8073  auto *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0->getOperand(1));
8074  auto *C2 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
8075  if (C1 && C2) {
8076  const APInt &C1Int = C1->getAPIntValue();
8077  APInt ShiftedC1Int = C1Int << C2->getAPIntValue();
8078 
8079  // We can materialise `c1 << c2` into an add immediate, so it's "free",
8080  // and the combine should happen, to potentially allow further combines
8081  // later.
8082  if (ShiftedC1Int.getMinSignedBits() <= 64 &&
8083  isLegalAddImmediate(ShiftedC1Int.getSExtValue()))
8084  return true;
8085 
8086  // We can materialise `c1` in an add immediate, so it's "free", and the
8087  // combine should be prevented.
8088  if (C1Int.getMinSignedBits() <= 64 &&
8089  isLegalAddImmediate(C1Int.getSExtValue()))
8090  return false;
8091 
8092  // Neither constant will fit into an immediate, so find materialisation
8093  // costs.
8094  int C1Cost = RISCVMatInt::getIntMatCost(C1Int, Ty.getSizeInBits(),
8095  Subtarget.getFeatureBits(),
8096  /*CompressionCost*/true);
8097  int ShiftedC1Cost = RISCVMatInt::getIntMatCost(
8098  ShiftedC1Int, Ty.getSizeInBits(), Subtarget.getFeatureBits(),
8099  /*CompressionCost*/true);
8100 
8101  // Materialising `c1` is cheaper than materialising `c1 << c2`, so the
8102  // combine should be prevented.
8103  if (C1Cost < ShiftedC1Cost)
8104  return false;
8105  }
8106  }
8107  return true;
8108 }
8109 
8110 bool RISCVTargetLowering::targetShrinkDemandedConstant(
8111  SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedBits, const APInt &DemandedElts,
8112  TargetLoweringOpt &TLO) const {
8113  // Delay this optimization as late as possible.
8114  if (!TLO.LegalOps)
8115  return false;
8116 
8117  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
8118  if (VT.isVector())
8119  return false;
8120 
8121  // Only handle AND for now.
8122  if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::AND)
8123  return false;
8124 
8125  ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1));
8126  if (!C)
8127  return false;
8128 
8129  const APInt &Mask = C->getAPIntValue();
8130 
8131  // Clear all non-demanded bits initially.
8132  APInt ShrunkMask = Mask & DemandedBits;
8133 
8134  // Try to make a smaller immediate by setting undemanded bits.
8135 
8136  APInt ExpandedMask = Mask | ~DemandedBits;
8137 
8138  auto IsLegalMask = [ShrunkMask, ExpandedMask](const APInt &Mask) -> bool {
8139  return ShrunkMask.isSubsetOf(Mask) && Mask.isSubsetOf(ExpandedMask);
8140  };
8141  auto UseMask = [Mask, Op, VT, &TLO](const APInt &NewMask) -> bool {
8142  if (NewMask == Mask)
8143  return true;
8144  SDLoc DL(Op);
8145  SDValue NewC = TLO.DAG.getConstant(NewMask, DL, VT);
8146  SDValue NewOp = TLO.DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(0), NewC);
8147  return TLO.CombineTo(Op, NewOp);
8148  };
8149 
8150  // If the shrunk mask fits in sign extended 12 bits, let the target
8151  // independent code apply it.
8152  if (ShrunkMask.isSignedIntN(12))
8153  return false;
8154 
8155  // Preserve (and X, 0xffff) when zext.h is supported.
8156  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZbb() || Subtarget.hasStdExtZbp()) {
8157  APInt NewMask = APInt(Mask.getBitWidth(), 0xffff);
8158  if (IsLegalMask(NewMask))
8159  return UseMask(NewMask);
8160  }
8161 
8162  // Try to preserve (and X, 0xffffffff), the (zext_inreg X, i32) pattern.
8163  if (VT == MVT::i64) {
8164  APInt NewMask = APInt(64, 0xffffffff);
8165  if (IsLegalMask(NewMask))
8166  return UseMask(NewMask);
8167  }
8168 
8169  // For the remaining optimizations, we need to be able to make a negative
8170  // number through a combination of mask and undemanded bits.
8171  if (!ExpandedMask.isNegative())
8172  return false;
8173 
8174  // What is the fewest number of bits we need to represent the negative number.
8175  unsigned MinSignedBits = ExpandedMask.getMinSignedBits();
8176 
8177  // Try to make a 12 bit negative immediate. If that fails try to make a 32
8178  // bit negative immediate unless the shrunk immediate already fits in 32 bits.
8179  APInt NewMask = ShrunkMask;
8180  if (MinSignedBits <= 12)
8181  NewMask.setBitsFrom(11);
8182  else if (MinSignedBits <= 32 && !ShrunkMask.isSignedIntN(32))
8183  NewMask.setBitsFrom(31);
8184  else
8185  return false;
8186 
8187  // Check that our new mask is a subset of the demanded mask.
8188  assert(IsLegalMask(NewMask));
8189  return UseMask(NewMask);
8190 }
8191 
8192 static void computeGREV(APInt &Src, unsigned ShAmt) {
8193  ShAmt &= Src.getBitWidth() - 1;
8194  uint64_t x = Src.getZExtValue();
8195  if (ShAmt & 1)
8196  x = ((x & 0x5555555555555555LL) << 1) | ((x & 0xAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALL) >> 1);
8197  if (ShAmt & 2)
8198  x = ((x & 0x3333333333333333LL) << 2) | ((x & 0xCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCLL) >> 2);
8199  if (ShAmt & 4)
8200  x = ((x & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0FLL) << 4) | ((x & 0xF0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0LL) >> 4);
8201  if (ShAmt & 8)
8202  x = ((x & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFLL) << 8) | ((x & 0xFF00FF00FF00FF00LL) >> 8);
8203  if (ShAmt & 16)
8204  x = ((x & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFLL) << 16) | ((x & 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000LL) >> 16);
8205  if (ShAmt & 32)
8206  x = ((x & 0x00000000FFFFFFFFLL) << 32) | ((x & 0xFFFFFFFF00000000LL) >> 32);
8207  Src = x;
8208 }
8209 
8210 void RISCVTargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForTargetNode(const SDValue Op,
8211  KnownBits &Known,
8212  const APInt &DemandedElts,
8213  const SelectionDAG &DAG,
8214  unsigned Depth) const {
8215  unsigned BitWidth = Known.getBitWidth();
8216  unsigned Opc = Op.getOpcode();
8217  assert((Opc >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END ||
8218  Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ||
8219  Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
8220  Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) &&
8221  "Should use MaskedValueIsZero if you don't know whether Op"
8222  " is a target node!");
8223 
8224  Known.resetAll();
8225  switch (Opc) {
8226  default: break;
8227  case RISCVISD::SELECT_CC: {
8228  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(4), Depth + 1);
8229  // If we don't know any bits, early out.
8230  if (Known.isUnknown())
8231  break;
8232  KnownBits Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(3), Depth + 1);
8233 
8234  // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
8235  Known = KnownBits::commonBits(Known, Known2);
8236  break;
8237  }
8238  case RISCVISD::REMUW: {
8239  KnownBits Known2;
8240  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
8241  Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
8242  // We only care about the lower 32 bits.
8243  Known = KnownBits::urem(Known.trunc(32), Known2.trunc(32));
8244  // Restore the original width by sign extending.
8245  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
8246  break;
8247  }
8248  case RISCVISD::DIVUW: {
8249  KnownBits Known2;
8250  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
8251  Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
8252  // We only care about the lower 32 bits.
8253  Known = KnownBits::udiv(Known.trunc(32), Known2.trunc(32));
8254  // Restore the original width by sign extending.
8255  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
8256  break;
8257  }
8258  case RISCVISD::CTZW: {
8259  KnownBits Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
8260  unsigned PossibleTZ = Known2.trunc(32).countMaxTrailingZeros();
8261  unsigned LowBits = Log2_32(PossibleTZ) + 1;
8262  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(LowBits);
8263  break;
8264  }
8265  case RISCVISD::CLZW: {
8266  KnownBits Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
8267  unsigned PossibleLZ = Known2.trunc(32).countMaxLeadingZeros();
8268  unsigned LowBits = Log2_32(PossibleLZ) + 1;
8269  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(LowBits);
8270  break;
8271  }
8272  case RISCVISD::GREV:
8273  case RISCVISD::GREVW: {
8274  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
8275  Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
8276  if (Opc == RISCVISD::GREVW)
8277  Known = Known.trunc(32);
8278  unsigned ShAmt = C->getZExtValue();
8279  computeGREV(Known.Zero, ShAmt);
8280  computeGREV(Known.One, ShAmt);
8281  if (Opc == RISCVISD::GREVW)
8282  Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
8283  }
8284  break;
8285  }
8286  case RISCVISD::READ_VLENB: {
8287  // If we know the minimum VLen from Zvl extensions, we can use that to
8288  // determine the trailing zeros of VLENB.
8289  // FIXME: Limit to 128 bit vectors until we have more testing.
8290  unsigned MinVLenB = std::min(128U, Subtarget.getMinVLen()) / 8;
8291  if (MinVLenB > 0)
8292  Known.Zero.setLowBits(Log2_32(MinVLenB));
8293  // We assume VLENB is no more than 65536 / 8 bytes.
8294  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(14);
8295  break;
8296  }
8297  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
8298  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: {
8299  unsigned IntNo =
8300  Op.getConstantOperandVal(Opc == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN ? 0 : 1);
8301  switch (IntNo) {
8302  default:
8303  // We can't do anything for most intrinsics.
8304  break;
8305  case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvli:
8306  case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvlimax:
8307  case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvli_opt:
8308  case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvlimax_opt:
8309  // Assume that VL output is positive and would fit in an int32_t.
8310  // TODO: VLEN might be capped at 16 bits in a future V spec update.
8311  if (BitWidth >= 32)
8312  Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(31);
8313  break;
8314  }
8315  break;
8316  }
8317  }
8318 }
8319 
8320 unsigned RISCVTargetLowering::ComputeNumSignBitsForTargetNode(
8321  SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts, const SelectionDAG &DAG,
8322  unsigned Depth) const {
8323  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
8324  default:
8325  break;
8326  case RISCVISD::SELECT_CC: {
8327  unsigned Tmp =
8328  DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(3), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
8329  if (Tmp == 1) return 1; // Early out.
8330  unsigned Tmp2 =
8331  DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(4), DemandedElts, Depth + 1);
8332  return std::min(Tmp, Tmp2);
8333  }
8334  case RISCVISD::SLLW:
8335  case RISCVISD::SRAW:
8336  case RISCVISD::SRLW:
8337  case RISCVISD::DIVW:
8338  case RISCVISD::DIVUW:
8339  case RISCVISD::REMUW:
8340  case RISCVISD::ROLW:
8341  case RISCVISD::RORW:
8342  case RISCVISD::GREVW:
8343  case RISCVISD::GORCW:
8344  case RISCVISD::FSLW:
8345  case RISCVISD::FSRW:
8346  case RISCVISD::SHFLW:
8347  case RISCVISD::UNSHFLW:
8348  case RISCVISD::BCOMPRESSW:
8349  case RISCVISD::BDECOMPRESSW:
8350  case RISCVISD::BFPW:
8351  case RISCVISD::FCVT_W_RV64:
8352  case RISCVISD::FCVT_WU_RV64:
8353  case RISCVISD::STRICT_FCVT_W_RV64:
8354  case RISCVISD::STRICT_FCVT_WU_RV64:
8355  // TODO: As the result is sign-extended, this is conservatively correct. A
8356  // more precise answer could be calculated for SRAW depending on known
8357  // bits in the shift amount.
8358  return 33;
8359  case RISCVISD::SHFL:
8360  case RISCVISD::UNSHFL: {
8361  // There is no SHFLIW, but a i64 SHFLI with bit 4 of the control word
8362  // cleared doesn't affect bit 31. The upper 32 bits will be shuffled, but
8363  // will stay within the upper 32 bits. If there were more than 32 sign bits
8364  // before there will be at least 33 sign bits after.
8365  if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::i64 &&
8366  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1)) &&
8367  (Op.getConstantOperandVal(1) & 0x10) == 0) {
8368  unsigned Tmp = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
8369  if (Tmp > 32)
8370  return 33;
8371  }
8372  break;
8373  }
8374  case RISCVISD::VMV_X_S: {
8375  // The number of sign bits of the scalar result is computed by obtaining the
8376  // element type of the input vector operand, subtracting its width from the
8377  // XLEN, and then adding one (sign bit within the element type). If the
8378  // element type is wider than XLen, the least-significant XLEN bits are
8379  // taken.
8380  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
8381  unsigned EltBits = Op.getOperand(0).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
8382  if (EltBits <= XLen)
8383  return XLen - EltBits + 1;
8384  break;
8385  }
8386  }
8387 
8388  return 1;
8389 }
8390 
8391 static MachineBasicBlock *emitReadCycleWidePseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
8392  MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
8393  assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::ReadCycleWide && "Unexpected instruction");
8394 
8395  // To read the 64-bit cycle CSR on a 32-bit target, we read the two halves.
8396  // Should the count have wrapped while it was being read, we need to try
8397  // again.
8398  // ...
8399  // read:
8400  // rdcycleh x3 # load high word of cycle
8401  // rdcycle x2 # load low word of cycle
8402  // rdcycleh x4 # load high word of cycle
8403  // bne x3, x4, read # check if high word reads match, otherwise try again
8404  // ...
8405 
8406  MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent();
8407  const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
8408  MachineFunction::iterator It = ++BB->getIterator();
8409 
8410  MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
8411  MF.insert(It, LoopMBB);
8412 
8413  MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
8414  MF.insert(It, DoneMBB);
8415 
8416  // Transfer the remainder of BB and its successor edges to DoneMBB.
8417  DoneMBB->splice(DoneMBB->begin(), BB,
8418  std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), BB->end());
8419  DoneMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(BB);
8420 
8421  BB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
8422 
8423  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
8424  Register ReadAgainReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
8425  Register LoReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
8426  Register HiReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
8427  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
8428 
8429  const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
8430  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::CSRRS), HiReg)
8431  .addImm(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("CYCLEH")->Encoding)
8432  .addReg(RISCV::X0);
8433  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::CSRRS), LoReg)
8434  .addImm(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("CYCLE")->Encoding)
8435  .addReg(RISCV::X0);
8436  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::CSRRS), ReadAgainReg)
8437  .addImm(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName("CYCLEH")->Encoding)
8438  .addReg(RISCV::X0);
8439 
8440  BuildMI(LoopMBB, DL, TII->get(RISCV::BNE))
8441  .addReg(HiReg)
8442  .addReg(ReadAgainReg)
8443  .addMBB(LoopMBB);
8444 
8445  LoopMBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
8446  LoopMBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
8447 
8448  MI.eraseFromParent();
8449 
8450  return DoneMBB;
8451 }
8452 
8453 static MachineBasicBlock *emitSplitF64Pseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
8454  MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
8455  assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::SplitF64Pseudo && "Unexpected instruction");
8456 
8457  MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent();
8458  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
8459  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
8460  const TargetRegisterInfo *RI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
8461  Register LoReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
8462  Register HiReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
8463  Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
8464  const TargetRegisterClass *SrcRC = &RISCV::FPR64RegClass;
8465  int FI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>()->getMoveF64FrameIndex(MF);
8466 
8467  TII.storeRegToStackSlot(*BB, MI, SrcReg, MI.getOperand(2).isKill(), FI, SrcRC,
8468  RI);
8469  MachinePointerInfo MPI = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI);
8470  MachineMemOperand *MMOLo =
8471  MF.getMachineMemOperand(MPI, MachineMemOperand::MOLoad, 4, Align(8));
8472  MachineMemOperand *MMOHi = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
8473  MPI.getWithOffset(4), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad, 4, Align(8));
8474  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::LW), LoReg)
8475  .addFrameIndex(FI)
8476  .addImm(0)
8477  .addMemOperand(MMOLo);
8478  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::LW), HiReg)
8479  .addFrameIndex(FI)
8480  .addImm(4)
8481  .addMemOperand(MMOHi);
8482  MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
8483  return BB;
8484 }
8485 
8486 static MachineBasicBlock *emitBuildPairF64Pseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
8487  MachineBasicBlock *BB) {
8488  assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::BuildPairF64Pseudo &&
8489  "Unexpected instruction");
8490 
8491  MachineFunction &MF = *BB->getParent();
8492  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
8493  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
8494  const TargetRegisterInfo *RI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo();
8495  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
8496  Register LoReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
8497  Register HiReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
8498  const TargetRegisterClass *DstRC = &RISCV::FPR64RegClass;
8499  int FI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>()->getMoveF64FrameIndex(MF);
8500 
8501  MachinePointerInfo MPI = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI);
8502  MachineMemOperand *MMOLo =
8503  MF.getMachineMemOperand(MPI, MachineMemOperand::MOStore, 4, Align(8));
8504  MachineMemOperand *MMOHi = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
8505  MPI.getWithOffset(4), MachineMemOperand::MOStore, 4, Align(8));
8506  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::SW))
8507  .addReg(LoReg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(1).isKill()))
8508  .addFrameIndex(FI)
8509  .addImm(0)
8510  .addMemOperand(MMOLo);
8511  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::SW))
8512  .addReg(HiReg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(2).isKill()))
8513  .addFrameIndex(FI)
8514  .addImm(4)
8515  .addMemOperand(MMOHi);
8516  TII.loadRegFromStackSlot(*BB, MI, DstReg, FI, DstRC, RI);
8517  MI.eraseFromParent(); // The pseudo instruction is gone now.
8518  return BB;
8519 }
8520 
8521 static bool isSelectPseudo(MachineInstr &MI) {
8522  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
8523  default:
8524  return false;
8525  case RISCV::Select_GPR_Using_CC_GPR:
8526  case RISCV::Select_FPR16_Using_CC_GPR:
8527  case RISCV::Select_FPR32_Using_CC_GPR:
8528  case RISCV::Select_FPR64_Using_CC_GPR:
8529  return true;
8530  }
8531 }
8532 
8533 static MachineBasicBlock *emitQuietFCMP(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *BB,
8534  unsigned RelOpcode, unsigned EqOpcode,
8535  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8536  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
8537  Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
8538  Register Src1Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
8539  Register Src2Reg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
8540  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = BB->getParent()->getRegInfo();
8541  Register SavedFFlags = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
8542  const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *BB->getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
8543 
8544  // Save the current FFLAGS.
8545  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::ReadFFLAGS), SavedFFlags);
8546 
8547  auto MIB = BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RelOpcode), DstReg)
8548  .addReg(Src1Reg)
8549  .addReg(Src2Reg);
8550  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
8551  MIB->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
8552 
8553  // Restore the FFLAGS.
8554  BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(RISCV::WriteFFLAGS))
8555  .addReg(SavedFFlags, RegState::Kill);
8556 
8557  // Issue a dummy FEQ opcode to raise exception for signaling NaNs.
8558  auto MIB2 = BuildMI(*BB, MI, DL, TII.get(EqOpcode), RISCV::X0)
8559  .addReg(Src1Reg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(1).isKill()))
8560  .addReg(Src2Reg, getKillRegState(MI.getOperand(2).isKill()));
8561  if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept))
8562  MIB2->setFlag(MachineInstr::MIFlag::NoFPExcept);
8563 
8564  // Erase the pseudoinstruction.
8565  MI.eraseFromParent();
8566  return BB;
8567 }
8568 
8569 static MachineBasicBlock *emitSelectPseudo(MachineInstr &MI,
8570  MachineBasicBlock *BB,
8571  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
8572  // To "insert" Select_* instructions, we actually have to insert the triangle
8573  // control-flow pattern. The incoming instructions know the destination vreg
8574  // to set, the condition code register to branch on, the true/false values to
8575  // select between, and the condcode to use to select the appropriate branch.
8576  //
8577  // We produce the following control flow:
8578  // HeadMBB
8579  // | \
8580  // | IfFalseMBB
8581  // | /
8582  // TailMBB
8583  //
8584  // When we find a sequence of selects we attempt to optimize their emission
8585  // by sharing the control flow. Currently we only handle cases where we have
8586  // multiple selects with the exact same condition (same LHS, RHS and CC).
8587  // The selects may be interleaved with other instructions if the other
8588  // instructions meet some requirements we deem safe:
8589  // - They are debug instructions. Otherwise,
8590  // - They do not have side-effects, do not access memory and their inputs do
8591  // not depend on the results of the select pseudo-instructions.
8592  // The TrueV/FalseV operands of the selects cannot depend on the result of
8593  // previous selects in the sequence.
8594  // These conditions could be further relaxed. See the X86 target for a
8595  // related approach and more information.
8596  Register LHS = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
8597  Register RHS = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
8598  auto CC = static_cast<RISCVCC::CondCode>(MI.getOperand(3).getImm());
8599 
8600  SmallVector<MachineInstr *, 4> SelectDebugValues;
8601  SmallSet<Register, 4> SelectDests;
8602  SelectDests.insert(MI.getOperand(0).getReg());
8603 
8604  MachineInstr *LastSelectPseudo = &MI;
8605 
8606  for (auto E = BB->end(), SequenceMBBI = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI);
8607  SequenceMBBI != E; ++SequenceMBBI) {
8608  if (SequenceMBBI->isDebugInstr())
8609  continue;
8610  else if (isSelectPseudo(*SequenceMBBI)) {
8611  if (SequenceMBBI->getOperand(1).getReg() != LHS ||
8612  SequenceMBBI->getOperand(2).getReg() != RHS ||
8613  SequenceMBBI->getOperand(3).getImm() != CC ||
8614  SelectDests.count(SequenceMBBI->getOperand(4).getReg()) ||
8615  SelectDests.count(SequenceMBBI->getOperand(5).getReg()))
8616  break;
8617  LastSelectPseudo = &*SequenceMBBI;
8618  SequenceMBBI->collectDebugValues(SelectDebugValues);
8619  SelectDests.insert(SequenceMBBI->getOperand(0).getReg());
8620  } else {
8621  if (SequenceMBBI->hasUnmodeledSideEffects() ||
8622  SequenceMBBI->mayLoadOrStore())
8623  break;
8624  if (llvm::any_of(SequenceMBBI->operands(), [&](MachineOperand &MO) {
8625  return MO.isReg() && MO.isUse() && SelectDests.count(MO.getReg());
8626  }))
8627  break;
8628  }
8629  }
8630 
8631  const RISCVInstrInfo &TII = *Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
8632  const BasicBlock *LLVM_BB = BB->getBasicBlock();
8633  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
8634  MachineFunction::iterator I = ++BB->getIterator();
8635 
8636  MachineBasicBlock *HeadMBB = BB;
8637  MachineFunction *F = BB->getParent();
8638  MachineBasicBlock *TailMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
8639  MachineBasicBlock *IfFalseMBB = F->CreateMachineBasicBlock(LLVM_BB);
8640 
8641  F->insert(I, IfFalseMBB);
8642  F->insert(I, TailMBB);
8643 
8644  // Transfer debug instructions associated with the selects to TailMBB.
8645  for (MachineInstr *DebugInstr : SelectDebugValues) {
8646  TailMBB->push_back(DebugInstr->removeFromParent());
8647  }
8648 
8649  // Move all instructions after the sequence to TailMBB.
8650  TailMBB->splice(TailMBB->end(), HeadMBB,
8651  std::next(LastSelectPseudo->getIterator()), HeadMBB->end());
8652  // Update machine-CFG edges by transferring all successors of the current
8653  // block to the new block which will contain the Phi nodes for the selects.
8654  TailMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(HeadMBB);
8655  // Set the successors for HeadMBB.
8656  HeadMBB->addSuccessor(IfFalseMBB);
8657  HeadMBB->addSuccessor(TailMBB);
8658 
8659  // Insert appropriate branch.
8660  BuildMI(HeadMBB, DL, TII.getBrCond(CC))
8661  .addReg(LHS)
8662  .addReg(RHS)
8663  .addMBB(TailMBB);
8664 
8665  // IfFalseMBB just falls through to TailMBB.
8666  IfFalseMBB->addSuccessor(TailMBB);
8667 
8668  // Create PHIs for all of the select pseudo-instructions.
8669  auto SelectMBBI = MI.getIterator();
8670  auto SelectEnd = std::next(LastSelectPseudo->getIterator());
8671  auto InsertionPoint = TailMBB->begin();
8672  while (SelectMBBI != SelectEnd) {
8673  auto Next = std::next(SelectMBBI);
8674  if (isSelectPseudo(*SelectMBBI)) {
8675  // %Result = phi [ %TrueValue, HeadMBB ], [ %FalseValue, IfFalseMBB ]
8676  BuildMI(*TailMBB, InsertionPoint, SelectMBBI->getDebugLoc(),
8677  TII.get(RISCV::PHI), SelectMBBI->getOperand(0).getReg())
8678  .addReg(SelectMBBI->getOperand(4).getReg())
8679  .addMBB(HeadMBB)
8680  .addReg(SelectMBBI->getOperand(5).getReg())
8681  .addMBB(IfFalseMBB);
8682  SelectMBBI->eraseFromParent();
8683  }
8684  SelectMBBI = Next;
8685  }
8686 
8687  F->getProperties().reset(MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoPHIs);
8688  return TailMBB;
8689 }
8690 
8691 MachineBasicBlock *
8692 RISCVTargetLowering::EmitInstrWithCustomInserter(MachineInstr &MI,
8693  MachineBasicBlock *BB) const {
8694  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
8695  default:
8696  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instr type to insert");
8697  case RISCV::ReadCycleWide:
8698  assert(!Subtarget.is64Bit() &&
8699  "ReadCycleWrite is only to be used on riscv32");
8700  return emitReadCycleWidePseudo(MI, BB);
8701  case RISCV::Select_GPR_Using_CC_GPR:
8702  case RISCV::Select_FPR16_Using_CC_GPR:
8703  case RISCV::Select_FPR32_Using_CC_GPR:
8704  case RISCV::Select_FPR64_Using_CC_GPR:
8705  return emitSelectPseudo(MI, BB, Subtarget);
8706  case RISCV::BuildPairF64Pseudo:
8707  return emitBuildPairF64Pseudo(MI, BB);
8708  case RISCV::SplitF64Pseudo:
8709  return emitSplitF64Pseudo(MI, BB);
8710  case RISCV::PseudoQuietFLE_H:
8711  return emitQuietFCMP(MI, BB, RISCV::FLE_H, RISCV::FEQ_H, Subtarget);
8712  case RISCV::PseudoQuietFLT_H:
8713  return emitQuietFCMP(MI, BB, RISCV::FLT_H, RISCV::FEQ_H, Subtarget);
8714  case RISCV::PseudoQuietFLE_S:
8715  return emitQuietFCMP(MI, BB, RISCV::FLE_S, RISCV::FEQ_S, Subtarget);
8716  case RISCV::PseudoQuietFLT_S:
8717  return emitQuietFCMP(MI, BB, RISCV::FLT_S, RISCV::FEQ_S, Subtarget);
8718  case RISCV::PseudoQuietFLE_D:
8719  return emitQuietFCMP(MI, BB, RISCV::FLE_D, RISCV::FEQ_D, Subtarget);
8720  case RISCV::PseudoQuietFLT_D:
8721  return emitQuietFCMP(MI, BB, RISCV::FLT_D, RISCV::FEQ_D, Subtarget);
8722  }
8723 }
8724 
8725 void RISCVTargetLowering::AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI,
8726  SDNode *Node) const {
8727  // Add FRM dependency to any instructions with dynamic rounding mode.
8728  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
8729  auto Idx = RISCV::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, RISCV::OpName::frm);
8730  if (Idx < 0)
8731  return;
8732  if (MI.getOperand(Idx).getImm() != RISCVFPRndMode::DYN)
8733  return;
8734  // If the instruction already reads FRM, don't add another read.
8735  if (MI.readsRegister(RISCV::FRM))
8736  return;
8737  MI.addOperand(
8738  MachineOperand::CreateReg(RISCV::FRM, /*isDef*/ false, /*isImp*/ true));
8739 }
8740 
8741 // Calling Convention Implementation.
8742 // The expectations for frontend ABI lowering vary from target to target.
8743 // Ideally, an LLVM frontend would be able to avoid worrying about many ABI
8744 // details, but this is a longer term goal. For now, we simply try to keep the
8745 // role of the frontend as simple and well-defined as possible. The rules can
8746 // be summarised as:
8747 // * Never split up large scalar arguments. We handle them here.
8748 // * If a hardfloat calling convention is being used, and the struct may be
8749 // passed in a pair of registers (fp+fp, int+fp), and both registers are
8750 // available, then pass as two separate arguments. If either the GPRs or FPRs
8751 // are exhausted, then pass according to the rule below.
8752 // * If a struct could never be passed in registers or directly in a stack
8753 // slot (as it is larger than 2*XLEN and the floating point rules don't
8754 // apply), then pass it using a pointer with the byval attribute.
8755 // * If a struct is less than 2*XLEN, then coerce to either a two-element
8756 // word-sized array or a 2*XLEN scalar (depending on alignment).
8757 // * The frontend can determine whether a struct is returned by reference or
8758 // not based on its size and fields. If it will be returned by reference, the
8759 // frontend must modify the prototype so a pointer with the sret annotation is
8760 // passed as the first argument. This is not necessary for large scalar
8761 // returns.
8762 // * Struct return values and varargs should be coerced to structs containing
8763 // register-size fields in the same situations they would be for fixed
8764 // arguments.
8765 
8766 static const MCPhysReg ArgGPRs[] = {
8767  RISCV::X10, RISCV::X11, RISCV::X12, RISCV::X13,
8768  RISCV::X14, RISCV::X15, RISCV::X16, RISCV::X17
8769 };
8770 static const MCPhysReg ArgFPR16s[] = {
8771  RISCV::F10_H, RISCV::F11_H, RISCV::F12_H, RISCV::F13_H,
8772  RISCV::F14_H, RISCV::F15_H, RISCV::F16_H, RISCV::F17_H
8773 };
8774 static const MCPhysReg ArgFPR32s[] = {
8775  RISCV::F10_F, RISCV::F11_F, RISCV::F12_F, RISCV::F13_F,
8776  RISCV::F14_F, RISCV::F15_F, RISCV::F16_F, RISCV::F17_F
8777 };
8778 static const MCPhysReg ArgFPR64s[] = {
8779  RISCV::F10_D, RISCV::F11_D, RISCV::F12_D, RISCV::F13_D,
8780  RISCV::F14_D, RISCV::F15_D, RISCV::F16_D, RISCV::F17_D
8781 };
8782 // This is an interim calling convention and it may be changed in the future.
8783 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRs[] = {
8784  RISCV::V8, RISCV::V9, RISCV::V10, RISCV::V11, RISCV::V12, RISCV::V13,
8785  RISCV::V14, RISCV::V15, RISCV::V16, RISCV::V17, RISCV::V18, RISCV::V19,
8786  RISCV::V20, RISCV::V21, RISCV::V22, RISCV::V23};
8787 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRM2s[] = {RISCV::V8M2, RISCV::V10M2, RISCV::V12M2,
8788  RISCV::V14M2, RISCV::V16M2, RISCV::V18M2,
8789  RISCV::V20M2, RISCV::V22M2};
8790 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRM4s[] = {RISCV::V8M4, RISCV::V12M4, RISCV::V16M4,
8791  RISCV::V20M4};
8792 static const MCPhysReg ArgVRM8s[] = {RISCV::V8M8, RISCV::V16M8};
8793 
8794 // Pass a 2*XLEN argument that has been split into two XLEN values through
8795 // registers or the stack as necessary.
8796 static bool CC_RISCVAssign2XLen(unsigned XLen, CCState &State, CCValAssign VA1,
8797  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags1, unsigned ValNo2,
8798  MVT ValVT2, MVT LocVT2,
8799  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags2) {
8800  unsigned XLenInBytes = XLen / 8;
8801  if (Register Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs)) {
8802  // At least one half can be passed via register.
8803  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(VA1.getValNo(), VA1.getValVT(), Reg,
8804  VA1.getLocVT(), CCValAssign::Full));
8805  } else {
8806  // Both halves must be passed on the stack, with proper alignment.
8807  Align StackAlign =
8808  std::max(Align(XLenInBytes), ArgFlags1.getNonZeroOrigAlign());
8809  State.addLoc(
8810  CCValAssign::getMem(VA1.getValNo(), VA1.getValVT(),
8811  State.AllocateStack(XLenInBytes, StackAlign),
8812  VA1.getLocVT(), CCValAssign::Full));
8813  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(
8814  ValNo2, ValVT2, State.AllocateStack(XLenInBytes, Align(XLenInBytes)),
8815  LocVT2, CCValAssign::Full));
8816  return false;
8817  }
8818 
8819  if (Register Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs)) {
8820  // The second half can also be passed via register.
8821  State.addLoc(
8822  CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo2, ValVT2, Reg, LocVT2, CCValAssign::Full));
8823  } else {
8824  // The second half is passed via the stack, without additional alignment.
8825  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(
8826  ValNo2, ValVT2, State.AllocateStack(XLenInBytes, Align(XLenInBytes)),
8827  LocVT2, CCValAssign::Full));
8828  }
8829 
8830  return false;
8831 }
8832 
8833 static unsigned allocateRVVReg(MVT ValVT, unsigned ValNo,
8834  Optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument,
8835  CCState &State, const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI) {
8836  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TLI.getRegClassFor(ValVT);
8837  if (RC == &RISCV::VRRegClass) {
8838  // Assign the first mask argument to V0.
8839  // This is an interim calling convention and it may be changed in the
8840  // future.
8841  if (FirstMaskArgument.hasValue() && ValNo == FirstMaskArgument.getValue())
8842  return State.AllocateReg(RISCV::V0);
8843  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRs);
8844  }
8845  if (RC == &RISCV::VRM2RegClass)
8846  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRM2s);
8847  if (RC == &RISCV::VRM4RegClass)
8848  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRM4s);
8849  if (RC == &RISCV::VRM8RegClass)
8850  return State.AllocateReg(ArgVRM8s);
8851  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled register class for ValueType");
8852 }
8853 
8854 // Implements the RISC-V calling convention. Returns true upon failure.
8855 static bool CC_RISCV(const DataLayout &DL, RISCVABI::ABI ABI, unsigned ValNo,
8856  MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo,
8857  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, CCState &State, bool IsFixed,
8858  bool IsRet, Type *OrigTy, const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI,
8859  Optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument) {
8860  unsigned XLen = DL.getLargestLegalIntTypeSizeInBits();
8861  assert(XLen == 32 || XLen == 64);
8862  MVT XLenVT = XLen == 32 ? MVT::i32 : MVT::i64;
8863 
8864  // Any return value split in to more than two values can't be returned
8865  // directly. Vectors are returned via the available vector registers.
8866  if (!LocVT.isVector() && IsRet && ValNo > 1)
8867  return true;
8868 
8869  // UseGPRForF16_F32 if targeting one of the soft-float ABIs, if passing a
8870  // variadic argument, or if no F16/F32 argument registers are available.
8871  bool UseGPRForF16_F32 = true;
8872  // UseGPRForF64 if targeting soft-float ABIs or an FLEN=32 ABI, if passing a
8873  // variadic argument, or if no F64 argument registers are available.
8874  bool UseGPRForF64 = true;
8875 
8876  switch (ABI) {
8877  default:
8878  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected ABI");
8879  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32:
8880  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64:
8881  break;
8882  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32F:
8883  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64F:
8884  UseGPRForF16_F32 = !IsFixed;
8885  break;
8886  case RISCVABI::ABI_ILP32D:
8887  case RISCVABI::ABI_LP64D:
8888  UseGPRForF16_F32 = !IsFixed;
8889  UseGPRForF64 = !IsFixed;
8890  break;
8891  }
8892 
8893  // FPR16, FPR32, and FPR64 alias each other.
8894  if (State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgFPR32s) == array_lengthof(ArgFPR32s)) {
8895  UseGPRForF16_F32 = true;
8896  UseGPRForF64 = true;
8897  }
8898 
8899  // From this point on, rely on UseGPRForF16_F32, UseGPRForF64 and
8900  // similar local variables rather than directly checking against the target
8901  // ABI.
8902 
8903  if (UseGPRForF16_F32 && (ValVT == MVT::f16 || ValVT == MVT::f32)) {
8904  LocVT = XLenVT;
8905  LocInfo = CCValAssign::BCvt;
8906  } else if (UseGPRForF64 && XLen == 64 && ValVT == MVT::f64) {
8907  LocVT = MVT::i64;
8908  LocInfo = CCValAssign::BCvt;
8909  }
8910 
8911  // If this is a variadic argument, the RISC-V calling convention requires
8912  // that it is assigned an 'even' or 'aligned' register if it has 8-byte
8913  // alignment (RV32) or 16-byte alignment (RV64). An aligned register should
8914  // be used regardless of whether the original argument was split during
8915  // legalisation or not. The argument will not be passed by registers if the
8916  // original type is larger than 2*XLEN, so the register alignment rule does
8917  // not apply.
8918  unsigned TwoXLenInBytes = (2 * XLen) / 8;
8919  if (!IsFixed && ArgFlags.getNonZeroOrigAlign() == TwoXLenInBytes &&
8920  DL.getTypeAllocSize(OrigTy) == TwoXLenInBytes) {
8921  unsigned RegIdx = State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgGPRs);
8922  // Skip 'odd' register if necessary.
8923  if (RegIdx != array_lengthof(ArgGPRs) && RegIdx % 2 == 1)
8924  State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs);
8925  }
8926 
8927  SmallVectorImpl<CCValAssign> &PendingLocs = State.getPendingLocs();
8928  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::ArgFlagsTy> &PendingArgFlags =
8929  State.getPendingArgFlags();
8930 
8931  assert(PendingLocs.size() == PendingArgFlags.size() &&
8932  "PendingLocs and PendingArgFlags out of sync");
8933 
8934  // Handle passing f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI or when floating point
8935  // registers are exhausted.
8936  if (UseGPRForF64 && XLen == 32 && ValVT == MVT::f64) {
8937  assert(!ArgFlags.isSplit() && PendingLocs.empty() &&
8938  "Can't lower f64 if it is split");
8939  // Depending on available argument GPRS, f64 may be passed in a pair of
8940  // GPRs, split between a GPR and the stack, or passed completely on the
8941  // stack. LowerCall/LowerFormalArguments/LowerReturn must recognise these
8942  // cases.
8943  Register Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs);
8944  LocVT = MVT::i32;
8945  if (!Reg) {
8946  unsigned StackOffset = State.AllocateStack(8, Align(8));
8947  State.addLoc(
8948  CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, StackOffset, LocVT, LocInfo));
8949  return false;
8950  }
8951  if (!State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs))
8952  State.AllocateStack(4, Align(4));
8953  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
8954  return false;
8955  }
8956 
8957  // Fixed-length vectors are located in the corresponding scalable-vector
8958  // container types.
8959  if (ValVT.isFixedLengthVector())
8960  LocVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(LocVT);
8961 
8962  // Split arguments might be passed indirectly, so keep track of the pending
8963  // values. Split vectors are passed via a mix of registers and indirectly, so
8964  // treat them as we would any other argument.
8965  if (ValVT.isScalarInteger() && (ArgFlags.isSplit() || !PendingLocs.empty())) {
8966  LocVT = XLenVT;
8967  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
8968  PendingLocs.push_back(
8969  CCValAssign::getPending(ValNo, ValVT, LocVT, LocInfo));
8970  PendingArgFlags.push_back(ArgFlags);
8971  if (!ArgFlags.isSplitEnd()) {
8972  return false;
8973  }
8974  }
8975 
8976  // If the split argument only had two elements, it should be passed directly
8977  // in registers or on the stack.
8978  if (ValVT.isScalarInteger() && ArgFlags.isSplitEnd() &&
8979  PendingLocs.size() <= 2) {
8980  assert(PendingLocs.size() == 2 && "Unexpected PendingLocs.size()");
8981  // Apply the normal calling convention rules to the first half of the
8982  // split argument.
8983  CCValAssign VA = PendingLocs[0];
8984  ISD::ArgFlagsTy AF = PendingArgFlags[0];
8985  PendingLocs.clear();
8986  PendingArgFlags.clear();
8987  return CC_RISCVAssign2XLen(XLen, State, VA, AF, ValNo, ValVT, LocVT,
8988  ArgFlags);
8989  }
8990 
8991  // Allocate to a register if possible, or else a stack slot.
8992  Register Reg;
8993  unsigned StoreSizeBytes = XLen / 8;
8994  Align StackAlign = Align(XLen / 8);
8995 
8996  if (ValVT == MVT::f16 && !UseGPRForF16_F32)
8997  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgFPR16s);
8998  else if (ValVT == MVT::f32 && !UseGPRForF16_F32)
8999  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgFPR32s);
9000  else if (ValVT == MVT::f64 && !UseGPRForF64)
9001  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgFPR64s);
9002  else if (ValVT.isVector()) {
9003  Reg = allocateRVVReg(ValVT, ValNo, FirstMaskArgument, State, TLI);
9004  if (!Reg) {
9005  // For return values, the vector must be passed fully via registers or
9006  // via the stack.
9007  // FIXME: The proposed vector ABI only mandates v8-v15 for return values,
9008  // but we're using all of them.
9009  if (IsRet)
9010  return true;
9011  // Try using a GPR to pass the address
9012  if ((Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs))) {
9013  LocVT = XLenVT;
9014  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
9015  } else if (ValVT.isScalableVector()) {
9016  LocVT = XLenVT;
9017  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
9018  } else {
9019  // Pass fixed-length vectors on the stack.
9020  LocVT = ValVT;
9021  StoreSizeBytes = ValVT.getStoreSize();
9022  // Align vectors to their element sizes, being careful for vXi1
9023  // vectors.
9024  StackAlign = MaybeAlign(ValVT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8).valueOrOne();
9025  }
9026  }
9027  } else {
9028  Reg = State.AllocateReg(ArgGPRs);
9029  }
9030 
9031  unsigned StackOffset =
9032  Reg ? 0 : State.AllocateStack(StoreSizeBytes, StackAlign);
9033 
9034  // If we reach this point and PendingLocs is non-empty, we must be at the
9035  // end of a split argument that must be passed indirectly.
9036  if (!PendingLocs.empty()) {
9037  assert(ArgFlags.isSplitEnd() && "Expected ArgFlags.isSplitEnd()");
9038  assert(PendingLocs.size() > 2 && "Unexpected PendingLocs.size()");
9039 
9040  for (auto &It : PendingLocs) {
9041  if (Reg)
9042  It.convertToReg(Reg);
9043  else
9044  It.convertToMem(StackOffset);
9045  State.addLoc(It);
9046  }
9047  PendingLocs.clear();
9048  PendingArgFlags.clear();
9049  return false;
9050  }
9051 
9052  assert((!UseGPRForF16_F32 || !UseGPRForF64 || LocVT == XLenVT ||
9053  (TLI.getSubtarget().hasVInstructions() && ValVT.isVector())) &&
9054  "Expected an XLenVT or vector types at this stage");
9055 
9056  if (Reg) {
9057  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9058  return false;
9059  }
9060 
9061  // When a floating-point value is passed on the stack, no bit-conversion is
9062  // needed.
9063  if (ValVT.isFloatingPoint()) {
9064  LocVT = ValVT;
9065  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Full;
9066  }
9067  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, StackOffset, LocVT, LocInfo));
9068  return false;
9069 }
9070 
9071 template <typename ArgTy>
9072 static Optional<unsigned> preAssignMask(const ArgTy &Args) {
9073  for (const auto &ArgIdx : enumerate(Args)) {
9074  MVT ArgVT = ArgIdx.value().VT;
9075  if (ArgVT.isVector() && ArgVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
9076  return ArgIdx.index();
9077  }
9078  return None;
9079 }
9080 
9081 void RISCVTargetLowering::analyzeInputArgs(
9082  MachineFunction &MF, CCState &CCInfo,
9083  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, bool IsRet,
9084  RISCVCCAssignFn Fn) const {
9085  unsigned NumArgs = Ins.size();
9086  FunctionType *FType = MF.getFunction().getFunctionType();
9087 
9088  Optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument;
9089  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
9090  FirstMaskArgument = preAssignMask(Ins);
9091 
9092  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; ++i) {
9093  MVT ArgVT = Ins[i].VT;
9094  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags = Ins[i].Flags;
9095 
9096  Type *ArgTy = nullptr;
9097  if (IsRet)
9098  ArgTy = FType->getReturnType();
9099  else if (Ins[i].isOrigArg())
9100  ArgTy = FType->getParamType(Ins[i].getOrigArgIndex());
9101 
9102  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().getTargetABI();
9103  if (Fn(MF.getDataLayout(), ABI, i, ArgVT, ArgVT, CCValAssign::Full,
9104  ArgFlags, CCInfo, /*IsFixed=*/true, IsRet, ArgTy, *this,
9105  FirstMaskArgument)) {
9106  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "InputArg #" << i << " has unhandled type "
9107  << EVT(ArgVT).getEVTString() << '\n');
9108  llvm_unreachable(nullptr);
9109  }
9110  }
9111 }
9112 
9113 void RISCVTargetLowering::analyzeOutputArgs(
9114  MachineFunction &MF, CCState &CCInfo,
9115  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs, bool IsRet,
9116  CallLoweringInfo *CLI, RISCVCCAssignFn Fn) const {
9117  unsigned NumArgs = Outs.size();
9118 
9119  Optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument;
9120  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
9121  FirstMaskArgument = preAssignMask(Outs);
9122 
9123  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; i++) {
9124  MVT ArgVT = Outs[i].VT;
9125  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags = Outs[i].Flags;
9126  Type *OrigTy = CLI ? CLI->getArgs()[Outs[i].OrigArgIndex].Ty : nullptr;
9127 
9128  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().getTargetABI();
9129  if (Fn(MF.getDataLayout(), ABI, i, ArgVT, ArgVT, CCValAssign::Full,
9130  ArgFlags, CCInfo, Outs[i].IsFixed, IsRet, OrigTy, *this,
9131  FirstMaskArgument)) {
9132  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "OutputArg #" << i << " has unhandled type "
9133  << EVT(ArgVT).getEVTString() << "\n");
9134  llvm_unreachable(nullptr);
9135  }
9136  }
9137 }
9138 
9139 // Convert Val to a ValVT. Should not be called for CCValAssign::Indirect
9140 // values.
9141 static SDValue convertLocVTToValVT(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Val,
9142  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL,
9143  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9144  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
9145  default:
9146  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CCValAssign::LocInfo");
9147  case CCValAssign::Full:
9148  if (VA.getValVT().isFixedLengthVector() && VA.getLocVT().isScalableVector())
9149  Val = convertFromScalableVector(VA.getValVT(), Val, DAG, Subtarget);
9150  break;
9151  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
9152  if (VA.getLocVT().isInteger() && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f16)
9153  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_H_X, DL, MVT::f16, Val);
9154  else if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i64 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f32)
9155  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_W_X_RV64, DL, MVT::f32, Val);
9156  else
9157  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VA.getValVT(), Val);
9158  break;
9159  }
9160  return Val;
9161 }
9162 
9163 // The caller is responsible for loading the full value if the argument is
9164 // passed with CCValAssign::Indirect.
9165 static SDValue unpackFromRegLoc(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
9166  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL,
9167  const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI) {
9168  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9169  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
9170  EVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
9171  SDValue Val;
9172  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TLI.getRegClassFor(LocVT.getSimpleVT());
9173  Register VReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
9174  RegInfo.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), VReg);
9175  Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VReg, LocVT);
9176 
9177  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
9178  return Val;
9179 
9180  return convertLocVTToValVT(DAG, Val, VA, DL, TLI.getSubtarget());
9181 }
9182 
9183 static SDValue convertValVTToLocVT(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Val,
9184  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL,
9185  const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) {
9186  EVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
9187 
9188  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
9189  default:
9190  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CCValAssign::LocInfo");
9191  case CCValAssign::Full:
9192  if (VA.getValVT().isFixedLengthVector() && LocVT.isScalableVector())
9193  Val = convertToScalableVector(LocVT, Val, DAG, Subtarget);
9194  break;
9195  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
9196  if (VA.getLocVT().isInteger() && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f16)
9197  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTH, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Val);
9198  else if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i64 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f32)
9199  Val = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::FMV_X_ANYEXTW_RV64, DL, MVT::i64, Val);
9200  else
9201  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LocVT, Val);
9202  break;
9203  }
9204  return Val;
9205 }
9206 
9207 // The caller is responsible for loading the full value if the argument is
9208 // passed with CCValAssign::Indirect.
9209 static SDValue unpackFromMemLoc(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
9210  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL) {
9211  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9212  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
9213  EVT LocVT = VA.getLocVT();
9214  EVT ValVT = VA.getValVT();
9215  EVT PtrVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(DAG.getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(0));
9216  if (ValVT.isScalableVector()) {
9217  // When the value is a scalable vector, we save the pointer which points to
9218  // the scalable vector value in the stack. The ValVT will be the pointer
9219  // type, instead of the scalable vector type.
9220  ValVT = LocVT;
9221  }
9222  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(ValVT.getStoreSize(), VA.getLocMemOffset(),
9223  /*IsImmutable=*/true);
9224  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT);
9225  SDValue Val;
9226 
9227  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType;
9228  switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
9229  default:
9230  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CCValAssign::LocInfo");
9231  case CCValAssign::Full:
9232  case CCValAssign::Indirect:
9233  case CCValAssign::BCvt:
9234  ExtType = ISD::NON_EXTLOAD;
9235  break;
9236  }
9237  Val = DAG.getExtLoad(
9238  ExtType, DL, LocVT, Chain, FIN,
9239  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI), ValVT);
9240  return Val;
9241 }
9242 
9243 static SDValue unpackF64OnRV32DSoftABI(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
9244  const CCValAssign &VA, const SDLoc &DL) {
9245  assert(VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64 &&
9246  "Unexpected VA");
9247  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9248  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
9249  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
9250 
9251  if (VA.isMemLoc()) {
9252  // f64 is passed on the stack.
9253  int FI =
9254  MFI.CreateFixedObject(8, VA.getLocMemOffset(), /*IsImmutable=*/true);
9255  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, MVT::i32);
9256  return DAG.getLoad(MVT::f64, DL, Chain, FIN,
9257  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI));
9258  }
9259 
9260  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Expected register VA assignment");
9261 
9262  Register LoVReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
9263  RegInfo.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), LoVReg);
9264  SDValue Lo = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, LoVReg, MVT::i32);
9265  SDValue Hi;
9266  if (VA.getLocReg() == RISCV::X17) {
9267  // Second half of f64 is passed on the stack.
9268  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(4, 0, /*IsImmutable=*/true);
9269  SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, MVT::i32);
9270  Hi = DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, DL, Chain, FIN,
9271  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI));
9272  } else {
9273  // Second half of f64 is passed in another GPR.
9274  Register HiVReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass);
9275  RegInfo.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg() + 1, HiVReg);
9276  Hi = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, HiVReg, MVT::i32);
9277  }
9278  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, Lo, Hi);
9279 }
9280 
9281 // FastCC has less than 1% performance improvement for some particular
9282 // benchmark. But theoretically, it may has benenfit for some cases.
9283 static bool CC_RISCV_FastCC(const DataLayout &DL, RISCVABI::ABI ABI,
9284  unsigned ValNo, MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT,
9285  CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo,
9286  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, CCState &State,
9287  bool IsFixed, bool IsRet, Type *OrigTy,
9288  const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI,
9289  Optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument) {
9290 
9291  // X5 and X6 might be used for save-restore libcall.
9292  static const MCPhysReg GPRList[] = {
9293  RISCV::X10, RISCV::X11, RISCV::X12, RISCV::X13, RISCV::X14,
9294  RISCV::X15, RISCV::X16, RISCV::X17, RISCV::X7, RISCV::X28,
9295  RISCV::X29, RISCV::X30, RISCV::X31};
9296 
9297  if (LocVT == MVT::i32 || LocVT == MVT::i64) {
9298  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(GPRList)) {
9299  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9300  return false;
9301  }
9302  }
9303 
9304  if (LocVT == MVT::f16) {
9305  static const MCPhysReg FPR16List[] = {
9306  RISCV::F10_H, RISCV::F11_H, RISCV::F12_H, RISCV::F13_H, RISCV::F14_H,
9307  RISCV::F15_H, RISCV::F16_H, RISCV::F17_H, RISCV::F0_H, RISCV::F1_H,
9308  RISCV::F2_H, RISCV::F3_H, RISCV::F4_H, RISCV::F5_H, RISCV::F6_H,
9309  RISCV::F7_H, RISCV::F28_H, RISCV::F29_H, RISCV::F30_H, RISCV::F31_H};
9310  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR16List)) {
9311  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9312  return false;
9313  }
9314  }
9315 
9316  if (LocVT == MVT::f32) {
9317  static const MCPhysReg FPR32List[] = {
9318  RISCV::F10_F, RISCV::F11_F, RISCV::F12_F, RISCV::F13_F, RISCV::F14_F,
9319  RISCV::F15_F, RISCV::F16_F, RISCV::F17_F, RISCV::F0_F, RISCV::F1_F,
9320  RISCV::F2_F, RISCV::F3_F, RISCV::F4_F, RISCV::F5_F, RISCV::F6_F,
9321  RISCV::F7_F, RISCV::F28_F, RISCV::F29_F, RISCV::F30_F, RISCV::F31_F};
9322  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR32List)) {
9323  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9324  return false;
9325  }
9326  }
9327 
9328  if (LocVT == MVT::f64) {
9329  static const MCPhysReg FPR64List[] = {
9330  RISCV::F10_D, RISCV::F11_D, RISCV::F12_D, RISCV::F13_D, RISCV::F14_D,
9331  RISCV::F15_D, RISCV::F16_D, RISCV::F17_D, RISCV::F0_D, RISCV::F1_D,
9332  RISCV::F2_D, RISCV::F3_D, RISCV::F4_D, RISCV::F5_D, RISCV::F6_D,
9333  RISCV::F7_D, RISCV::F28_D, RISCV::F29_D, RISCV::F30_D, RISCV::F31_D};
9334  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR64List)) {
9335  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9336  return false;
9337  }
9338  }
9339 
9340  if (LocVT == MVT::i32 || LocVT == MVT::f32) {
9341  unsigned Offset4 = State.AllocateStack(4, Align(4));
9342  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset4, LocVT, LocInfo));
9343  return false;
9344  }
9345 
9346  if (LocVT == MVT::i64 || LocVT == MVT::f64) {
9347  unsigned Offset5 = State.AllocateStack(8, Align(8));
9348  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset5, LocVT, LocInfo));
9349  return false;
9350  }
9351 
9352  if (LocVT.isVector()) {
9353  if (unsigned Reg =
9354  allocateRVVReg(ValVT, ValNo, FirstMaskArgument, State, TLI)) {
9355  // Fixed-length vectors are located in the corresponding scalable-vector
9356  // container types.
9357  if (ValVT.isFixedLengthVector())
9358  LocVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(LocVT);
9359  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9360  } else {
9361  // Try and pass the address via a "fast" GPR.
9362  if (unsigned GPRReg = State.AllocateReg(GPRList)) {
9363  LocInfo = CCValAssign::Indirect;
9364  LocVT = TLI.getSubtarget().getXLenVT();
9365  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, GPRReg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9366  } else if (ValVT.isFixedLengthVector()) {
9367  auto StackAlign =
9368  MaybeAlign(ValVT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8).valueOrOne();
9369  unsigned StackOffset =
9370  State.AllocateStack(ValVT.getStoreSize(), StackAlign);
9371  State.addLoc(
9372  CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, StackOffset, LocVT, LocInfo));
9373  } else {
9374  // Can't pass scalable vectors on the stack.
9375  return true;
9376  }
9377  }
9378 
9379  return false;
9380  }
9381 
9382  return true; // CC didn't match.
9383 }
9384 
9385 static bool CC_RISCV_GHC(unsigned ValNo, MVT ValVT, MVT LocVT,
9386  CCValAssign::LocInfo LocInfo,
9387  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags, CCState &State) {
9388 
9389  if (LocVT == MVT::i32 || LocVT == MVT::i64) {
9390  // Pass in STG registers: Base, Sp, Hp, R1, R2, R3, R4, R5, R6, R7, SpLim
9391  // s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11
9392  static const MCPhysReg GPRList[] = {
9393  RISCV::X9, RISCV::X18, RISCV::X19, RISCV::X20, RISCV::X21, RISCV::X22,
9394  RISCV::X23, RISCV::X24, RISCV::X25, RISCV::X26, RISCV::X27};
9395  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(GPRList)) {
9396  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9397  return false;
9398  }
9399  }
9400 
9401  if (LocVT == MVT::f32) {
9402  // Pass in STG registers: F1, ..., F6
9403  // fs0 ... fs5
9404  static const MCPhysReg FPR32List[] = {RISCV::F8_F, RISCV::F9_F,
9405  RISCV::F18_F, RISCV::F19_F,
9406  RISCV::F20_F, RISCV::F21_F};
9407  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR32List)) {
9408  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9409  return false;
9410  }
9411  }
9412 
9413  if (LocVT == MVT::f64) {
9414  // Pass in STG registers: D1, ..., D6
9415  // fs6 ... fs11
9416  static const MCPhysReg FPR64List[] = {RISCV::F22_D, RISCV::F23_D,
9417  RISCV::F24_D, RISCV::F25_D,
9418  RISCV::F26_D, RISCV::F27_D};
9419  if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(FPR64List)) {
9420  State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
9421  return false;
9422  }
9423  }
9424 
9425  report_fatal_error("No registers left in GHC calling convention");
9426  return true;
9427 }
9428 
9429 // Transform physical registers into virtual registers.
9430 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments(
9431  SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
9432  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
9433  SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
9434 
9435  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9436 
9437  switch (CallConv) {
9438  default:
9439  report_fatal_error("Unsupported calling convention");
9440  case CallingConv::C:
9441  case CallingConv::Fast:
9442  break;
9443  case CallingConv::GHC:
9444  if (!MF.getSubtarget().getFeatureBits()[RISCV::FeatureStdExtF] ||
9445  !MF.getSubtarget().getFeatureBits()[RISCV::FeatureStdExtD])
9446  report_fatal_error(
9447  "GHC calling convention requires the F and D instruction set extensions");
9448  }
9449 
9450  const Function &Func = MF.getFunction();
9451  if (Func.hasFnAttribute("interrupt")) {
9452  if (!Func.arg_empty())
9453  report_fatal_error(
9454  "Functions with the interrupt attribute cannot have arguments!");
9455 
9456  StringRef Kind =
9457  MF.getFunction().getFnAttribute("interrupt").getValueAsString();
9458 
9459  if (!(Kind == "user" || Kind == "supervisor" || Kind == "machine"))
9460  report_fatal_error(
9461  "Function interrupt attribute argument not supported!");
9462  }
9463 
9464  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
9465  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
9466  unsigned XLenInBytes = Subtarget.getXLen() / 8;
9467  // Used with vargs to acumulate store chains.
9468  std::vector<SDValue> OutChains;
9469 
9470  // Assign locations to all of the incoming arguments.
9471  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
9472  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext());
9473 
9474  if (CallConv == CallingConv::GHC)
9475  CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_RISCV_GHC);
9476  else
