9477  analyzeInputArgs(MF, CCInfo, Ins, /*IsRet=*/false,
9478  CallConv == CallingConv::Fast ? CC_RISCV_FastCC
9479  : CC_RISCV);
9480 
9481  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
9482  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
9483  SDValue ArgValue;
9484  // Passing f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI must be handled as a special
9485  // case.
9486  if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64)
9487  ArgValue = unpackF64OnRV32DSoftABI(DAG, Chain, VA, DL);
9488  else if (VA.isRegLoc())
9489  ArgValue = unpackFromRegLoc(DAG, Chain, VA, DL, *this);
9490  else
9491  ArgValue = unpackFromMemLoc(DAG, Chain, VA, DL);
9492 
9493  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect) {
9494  // If the original argument was split and passed by reference (e.g. i128
9495  // on RV32), we need to load all parts of it here (using the same
9496  // address). Vectors may be partly split to registers and partly to the
9497  // stack, in which case the base address is partly offset and subsequent
9498  // stores are relative to that.
9499  InVals.push_back(DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), DL, Chain, ArgValue,
9500  MachinePointerInfo()));
9501  unsigned ArgIndex = Ins[i].OrigArgIndex;
9502  unsigned ArgPartOffset = Ins[i].PartOffset;
9503  assert(VA.getValVT().isVector() || ArgPartOffset == 0);
9504  while (i + 1 != e && Ins[i + 1].OrigArgIndex == ArgIndex) {
9505  CCValAssign &PartVA = ArgLocs[i + 1];
9506  unsigned PartOffset = Ins[i + 1].PartOffset - ArgPartOffset;
9507  SDValue Offset = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(PartOffset, DL);
9508  if (PartVA.getValVT().isScalableVector())
9509  Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, Offset);
9510  SDValue Address = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, ArgValue, Offset);
9511  InVals.push_back(DAG.getLoad(PartVA.getValVT(), DL, Chain, Address,
9512  MachinePointerInfo()));
9513  ++i;
9514  }
9515  continue;
9516  }
9517  InVals.push_back(ArgValue);
9518  }
9519 
9520  if (IsVarArg) {
9521  ArrayRef<MCPhysReg> ArgRegs = makeArrayRef(ArgGPRs);
9522  unsigned Idx = CCInfo.getFirstUnallocated(ArgRegs);
9523  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &RISCV::GPRRegClass;
9524  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
9525  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
9526  RISCVMachineFunctionInfo *RVFI = MF.getInfo<RISCVMachineFunctionInfo>();
9527 
9528  // Offset of the first variable argument from stack pointer, and size of
9529  // the vararg save area. For now, the varargs save area is either zero or
9530  // large enough to hold a0-a7.
9531  int VaArgOffset, VarArgsSaveSize;
9532 
9533  // If all registers are allocated, then all varargs must be passed on the
9534  // stack and we don't need to save any argregs.
9535  if (ArgRegs.size() == Idx) {
9536  VaArgOffset = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
9537  VarArgsSaveSize = 0;
9538  } else {
9539  VarArgsSaveSize = XLenInBytes * (ArgRegs.size() - Idx);
9540  VaArgOffset = -VarArgsSaveSize;
9541  }
9542 
9543  // Record the frame index of the first variable argument
9544  // which is a value necessary to VASTART.
9545  int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(XLenInBytes, VaArgOffset, true);
9546  RVFI->setVarArgsFrameIndex(FI);
9547 
9548  // If saving an odd number of registers then create an extra stack slot to
9549  // ensure that the frame pointer is 2*XLEN-aligned, which in turn ensures
9550  // offsets to even-numbered registered remain 2*XLEN-aligned.
9551  if (Idx % 2) {
9552  MFI.CreateFixedObject(XLenInBytes, VaArgOffset - (int)XLenInBytes, true);
9553  VarArgsSaveSize += XLenInBytes;
9554  }
9555 
9556  // Copy the integer registers that may have been used for passing varargs
9557  // to the vararg save area.
9558  for (unsigned I = Idx; I < ArgRegs.size();
9559  ++I, VaArgOffset += XLenInBytes) {
9560  const Register Reg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(RC);
9561  RegInfo.addLiveIn(ArgRegs[I], Reg);
9562  SDValue ArgValue = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, XLenVT);
9563  FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(XLenInBytes, VaArgOffset, true);
9564  SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
9565  SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, PtrOff,
9566  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI));
9567  cast<StoreSDNode>(Store.getNode())
9568  ->getMemOperand()
9569  ->setValue((Value *)nullptr);
9570  OutChains.push_back(Store);
9571  }
9572  RVFI->setVarArgsSaveSize(VarArgsSaveSize);
9573  }
9574 
9575  // All stores are grouped in one node to allow the matching between
9576  // the size of Ins and InVals. This only happens for vararg functions.
9577  if (!OutChains.empty()) {
9578  OutChains.push_back(Chain);
9579  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, OutChains);
9580  }
9581 
9582  return Chain;
9583 }
9584 
9585 /// isEligibleForTailCallOptimization - Check whether the call is eligible
9586 /// for tail call optimization.
9587 /// Note: This is modelled after ARM's IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization.
9588 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
9589  CCState &CCInfo, CallLoweringInfo &CLI, MachineFunction &MF,
9590  const SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> &ArgLocs) const {
9591 
9592  auto &Callee = CLI.Callee;
9593  auto CalleeCC = CLI.CallConv;
9594  auto &Outs = CLI.Outs;
9595  auto &Caller = MF.getFunction();
9596  auto CallerCC = Caller.getCallingConv();
9597 
9598  // Exception-handling functions need a special set of instructions to
9599  // indicate a return to the hardware. Tail-calling another function would
9600  // probably break this.
9601  // TODO: The "interrupt" attribute isn't currently defined by RISC-V. This
9602  // should be expanded as new function attributes are introduced.
9603  if (Caller.hasFnAttribute("interrupt"))
9604  return false;
9605 
9606  // Do not tail call opt if the stack is used to pass parameters.
9607  if (CCInfo.getNextStackOffset() != 0)
9608  return false;
9609 
9610  // Do not tail call opt if any parameters need to be passed indirectly.
9611  // Since long doubles (fp128) and i128 are larger than 2*XLEN, they are
9612  // passed indirectly. So the address of the value will be passed in a
9613  // register, or if not available, then the address is put on the stack. In
9614  // order to pass indirectly, space on the stack often needs to be allocated
9615  // in order to store the value. In this case the CCInfo.getNextStackOffset()
9616  // != 0 check is not enough and we need to check if any CCValAssign ArgsLocs
9617  // are passed CCValAssign::Indirect.
9618  for (auto &VA : ArgLocs)
9619  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect)
9620  return false;
9621 
9622  // Do not tail call opt if either caller or callee uses struct return
9623  // semantics.
9624  auto IsCallerStructRet = Caller.hasStructRetAttr();
9625  auto IsCalleeStructRet = Outs.empty() ? false : Outs[0].Flags.isSRet();
9626  if (IsCallerStructRet || IsCalleeStructRet)
9627  return false;
9628 
9629  // Externally-defined functions with weak linkage should not be
9630  // tail-called. The behaviour of branch instructions in this situation (as
9631  // used for tail calls) is implementation-defined, so we cannot rely on the
9632  // linker replacing the tail call with a return.
9633  if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
9634  const GlobalValue *GV = G->getGlobal();
9635  if (GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
9636  return false;
9637  }
9638 
9639  // The callee has to preserve all registers the caller needs to preserve.
9640  const RISCVRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
9641  const uint32_t *CallerPreserved = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallerCC);
9642  if (CalleeCC != CallerCC) {
9643  const uint32_t *CalleePreserved = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CalleeCC);
9644  if (!TRI->regmaskSubsetEqual(CallerPreserved, CalleePreserved))
9645  return false;
9646  }
9647 
9648  // Byval parameters hand the function a pointer directly into the stack area
9649  // we want to reuse during a tail call. Working around this *is* possible
9650  // but less efficient and uglier in LowerCall.
9651  for (auto &Arg : Outs)
9652  if (Arg.Flags.isByVal())
9653  return false;
9654 
9655  return true;
9656 }
9657 
9658 static Align getPrefTypeAlign(EVT VT, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
9659  return DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(
9660  VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()));
9661 }
9662 
9663 // Lower a call to a callseq_start + CALL + callseq_end chain, and add input
9664 // and output parameter nodes.
9665 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::LowerCall(CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
9666  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
9667  SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
9668  SDLoc &DL = CLI.DL;
9669  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs = CLI.Outs;
9670  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals = CLI.OutVals;
9671  SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins = CLI.Ins;
9672  SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
9673  SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
9674  bool &IsTailCall = CLI.IsTailCall;
9675  CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv;
9676  bool IsVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg;
9677  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
9678  MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT();
9679 
9680  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9681 
9682  // Analyze the operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
9683  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
9684  CCState ArgCCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext());
9685 
9686  if (CallConv == CallingConv::GHC)
9687  ArgCCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_RISCV_GHC);
9688  else
9689  analyzeOutputArgs(MF, ArgCCInfo, Outs, /*IsRet=*/false, &CLI,
9690  CallConv == CallingConv::Fast ? CC_RISCV_FastCC
9691  : CC_RISCV);
9692 
9693  // Check if it's really possible to do a tail call.
9694  if (IsTailCall)
9695  IsTailCall = isEligibleForTailCallOptimization(ArgCCInfo, CLI, MF, ArgLocs);
9696 
9697  if (IsTailCall)
9698  ++NumTailCalls;
9699  else if (CLI.CB && CLI.CB->isMustTailCall())
9700  report_fatal_error("failed to perform tail call elimination on a call "
9701  "site marked musttail");
9702 
9703  // Get a count of how many bytes are to be pushed on the stack.
9704  unsigned NumBytes = ArgCCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
9705 
9706  // Create local copies for byval args
9707  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ByValArgs;
9708  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Outs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
9709  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
9710  if (!Flags.isByVal())
9711  continue;
9712 
9713  SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
9714  unsigned Size = Flags.getByValSize();
9715  Align Alignment = Flags.getNonZeroByValAlign();
9716 
9717  int FI =
9718  MF.getFrameInfo().CreateStackObject(Size, Alignment, /*isSS=*/false);
9719  SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
9720  SDValue SizeNode = DAG.getConstant(Size, DL, XLenVT);
9721 
9722  Chain = DAG.getMemcpy(Chain, DL, FIPtr, Arg, SizeNode, Alignment,
9723  /*IsVolatile=*/false,
9724  /*AlwaysInline=*/false, IsTailCall,
9725  MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo());
9726  ByValArgs.push_back(FIPtr);
9727  }
9728 
9729  if (!IsTailCall)
9730  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, NumBytes, 0, CLI.DL);
9731 
9732  // Copy argument values to their designated locations.
9733  SmallVector<std::pair<Register, SDValue>, 8> RegsToPass;
9734  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
9735  SDValue StackPtr;
9736  for (unsigned i = 0, j = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
9737  CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
9738  SDValue ArgValue = OutVals[i];
9739  ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
9740 
9741  // Handle passing f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI as a special case.
9742  bool IsF64OnRV32DSoftABI =
9743  VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64;
9744  if (IsF64OnRV32DSoftABI && VA.isRegLoc()) {
9745  SDValue SplitF64 = DAG.getNode(
9746  RISCVISD::SplitF64, DL, DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32), ArgValue);
9747  SDValue Lo = SplitF64.getValue(0);
9748  SDValue Hi = SplitF64.getValue(1);
9749 
9750  Register RegLo = VA.getLocReg();
9751  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(RegLo, Lo));
9752 
9753  if (RegLo == RISCV::X17) {
9754  // Second half of f64 is passed on the stack.
9755  // Work out the address of the stack slot.
9756  if (!StackPtr.getNode())
9757  StackPtr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RISCV::X2, PtrVT);
9758  // Emit the store.
9759  MemOpChains.push_back(
9760  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Hi, StackPtr, MachinePointerInfo()));
9761  } else {
9762  // Second half of f64 is passed in another GPR.
9763  assert(RegLo < RISCV::X31 && "Invalid register pair");
9764  Register RegHigh = RegLo + 1;
9765  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(RegHigh, Hi));
9766  }
9767  continue;
9768  }
9769 
9770  // IsF64OnRV32DSoftABI && VA.isMemLoc() is handled below in the same way
9771  // as any other MemLoc.
9772 
9773  // Promote the value if needed.
9774  // For now, only handle fully promoted and indirect arguments.
9775  if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::Indirect) {
9776  // Store the argument in a stack slot and pass its address.
9777  Align StackAlign =
9778  std::max(getPrefTypeAlign(Outs[i].ArgVT, DAG),
9779  getPrefTypeAlign(ArgValue.getValueType(), DAG));
9780  TypeSize StoredSize = ArgValue.getValueType().getStoreSize();
9781  // If the original argument was split (e.g. i128), we need
9782  // to store the required parts of it here (and pass just one address).
9783  // Vectors may be partly split to registers and partly to the stack, in
9784  // which case the base address is partly offset and subsequent stores are
9785  // relative to that.
9786  unsigned ArgIndex = Outs[i].OrigArgIndex;
9787  unsigned ArgPartOffset = Outs[i].PartOffset;
9788  assert(VA.getValVT().isVector() || ArgPartOffset == 0);
9789  // Calculate the total size to store. We don't have access to what we're
9790  // actually storing other than performing the loop and collecting the
9791  // info.
9792  SmallVector<std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>> Parts;
9793  while (i + 1 != e && Outs[i + 1].OrigArgIndex == ArgIndex) {
9794  SDValue PartValue = OutVals[i + 1];
9795  unsigned PartOffset = Outs[i + 1].PartOffset - ArgPartOffset;
9796  SDValue Offset = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(PartOffset, DL);
9797  EVT PartVT = PartValue.getValueType();
9798  if (PartVT.isScalableVector())
9799  Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSCALE, DL, XLenVT, Offset);
9800  StoredSize += PartVT.getStoreSize();
9801  StackAlign = std::max(StackAlign, getPrefTypeAlign(PartVT, DAG));
9802  Parts.push_back(std::make_pair(PartValue, Offset));
9803  ++i;
9804  }
9805  SDValue SpillSlot = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(StoredSize, StackAlign);
9806  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(SpillSlot)->getIndex();
9807  MemOpChains.push_back(
9808  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, SpillSlot,
9809  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI)));
9810  for (const auto &Part : Parts) {
9811  SDValue PartValue = Part.first;
9812  SDValue PartOffset = Part.second;
9813  SDValue Address =
9814  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, SpillSlot, PartOffset);
9815  MemOpChains.push_back(
9816  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, PartValue, Address,
9817  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI)));
9818  }
9819  ArgValue = SpillSlot;
9820  } else {
9821  ArgValue = convertValVTToLocVT(DAG, ArgValue, VA, DL, Subtarget);
9822  }
9823 
9824  // Use local copy if it is a byval arg.
9825  if (Flags.isByVal())
9826  ArgValue = ByValArgs[j++];
9827 
9828  if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
9829  // Queue up the argument copies and emit them at the end.
9830  RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), ArgValue));
9831  } else {
9832  assert(VA.isMemLoc() && "Argument not register or memory");
9833  assert(!IsTailCall && "Tail call not allowed if stack is used "
9834  "for passing parameters");
9835 
9836  // Work out the address of the stack slot.
9837  if (!StackPtr.getNode())
9838  StackPtr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, RISCV::X2, PtrVT);
9839  SDValue Address =
9840  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr,
9841  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(VA.getLocMemOffset(), DL));
9842 
9843  // Emit the store.
9844  MemOpChains.push_back(
9845  DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, ArgValue, Address, MachinePointerInfo()));
9846  }
9847  }
9848 
9849  // Join the stores, which are independent of one another.
9850  if (!MemOpChains.empty())
9851  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
9852 
9853  SDValue Glue;
9854 
9855  // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes, chained and glued together.
9856  for (auto &Reg : RegsToPass) {
9857  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, Reg.first, Reg.second, Glue);
9858  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
9859  }
9860 
9861  // Validate that none of the argument registers have been marked as
9862  // reserved, if so report an error. Do the same for the return address if this
9863  // is not a tailcall.
9864  validateCCReservedRegs(RegsToPass, MF);
9865  if (!IsTailCall &&
9866  MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().isRegisterReservedByUser(RISCV::X1))
9867  MF.getFunction().getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
9868  MF.getFunction(),
9869  "Return address register required, but has been reserved."});
9870 
9871  // If the callee is a GlobalAddress/ExternalSymbol node, turn it into a
9872  // TargetGlobalAddress/TargetExternalSymbol node so that legalize won't
9873  // split it and then direct call can be matched by PseudoCALL.
9874  if (GlobalAddressSDNode *S = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
9875  const GlobalValue *GV = S->getGlobal();
9876 
9877  unsigned OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_CALL;
9878  if (!getTargetMachine().shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*GV->getParent(), GV))
9879  OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_PLT;
9880 
9881  Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, PtrVT, 0, OpFlags);
9882  } else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *S = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
9883  unsigned OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_CALL;
9884 
9885  if (!getTargetMachine().shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*MF.getFunction().getParent(),
9886  nullptr))
9887  OpFlags = RISCVII::MO_PLT;
9888 
9889  Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol(S->getSymbol(), PtrVT, OpFlags);
9890  }
9891 
9892  // The first call operand is the chain and the second is the target address.
9893  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
9894  Ops.push_back(Chain);
9895  Ops.push_back(Callee);
9896 
9897  // Add argument registers to the end of the list so that they are
9898  // known live into the call.
9899  for (auto &Reg : RegsToPass)
9900  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegister(Reg.first, Reg.second.getValueType()));
9901 
9902  if (!IsTailCall) {
9903  // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers.
9904  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
9905  const uint32_t *Mask = TRI->getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallConv);
9906  assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
9907  Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
9908  }
9909 
9910  // Glue the call to the argument copies, if any.
9911  if (Glue.getNode())
9912  Ops.push_back(Glue);
9913 
9914  // Emit the call.
9915  SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
9916 
9917  if (IsTailCall) {
9918  MF.getFrameInfo().setHasTailCall();
9919  return DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::TAIL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
9920  }
9921 
9922  Chain = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::CALL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
9923  DAG.addNoMergeSiteInfo(Chain.getNode(), CLI.NoMerge);
9924  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
9925 
9926  // Mark the end of the call, which is glued to the call itself.
9927  Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain,
9928  DAG.getConstant(NumBytes, DL, PtrVT, true),
9929  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, PtrVT, true),
9930  Glue, DL);
9931  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
9932 
9933  // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
9934  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
9935  CCState RetCCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, *DAG.getContext());
9936  analyzeInputArgs(MF, RetCCInfo, Ins, /*IsRet=*/true, CC_RISCV);
9937 
9938  // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
9939  for (auto &VA : RVLocs) {
9940  // Copy the value out
9941  SDValue RetValue =
9942  DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT(), Glue);
9943  // Glue the RetValue to the end of the call sequence
9944  Chain = RetValue.getValue(1);
9945  Glue = RetValue.getValue(2);
9946 
9947  if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64) {
9948  assert(VA.getLocReg() == ArgGPRs[0] && "Unexpected reg assignment");
9949  SDValue RetValue2 =
9950  DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, ArgGPRs[1], MVT::i32, Glue);
9951  Chain = RetValue2.getValue(1);
9952  Glue = RetValue2.getValue(2);
9953  RetValue = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::BuildPairF64, DL, MVT::f64, RetValue,
9954  RetValue2);
9955  }
9956 
9957  RetValue = convertLocVTToValVT(DAG, RetValue, VA, DL, Subtarget);
9958 
9959  InVals.push_back(RetValue);
9960  }
9961 
9962  return Chain;
9963 }
9964 
9965 bool RISCVTargetLowering::CanLowerReturn(
9966  CallingConv::ID CallConv, MachineFunction &MF, bool IsVarArg,
9967  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs, LLVMContext &Context) const {
9968  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
9969  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, Context);
9970 
9971  Optional<unsigned> FirstMaskArgument;
9972  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions())
9973  FirstMaskArgument = preAssignMask(Outs);
9974 
9975  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Outs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
9976  MVT VT = Outs[i].VT;
9977  ISD::ArgFlagsTy ArgFlags = Outs[i].Flags;
9978  RISCVABI::ABI ABI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>().getTargetABI();
9979  if (CC_RISCV(MF.getDataLayout(), ABI, i, VT, VT, CCValAssign::Full,
9980  ArgFlags, CCInfo, /*IsFixed=*/true, /*IsRet=*/true, nullptr,
9981  *this, FirstMaskArgument))
9982  return false;
9983  }
9984  return true;
9985 }
9986 
9987 SDValue
9988 RISCVTargetLowering::LowerReturn(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
9989  bool IsVarArg,
9990  const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
9991  const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
9992  const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9993  const MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9994  const RISCVSubtarget &STI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>();
9995 
9996  // Stores the assignment of the return value to a location.
9997  SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
9998 
9999  // Info about the registers and stack slot.
10000  CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
10001  *DAG.getContext());
10002 
10003  analyzeOutputArgs(DAG.getMachineFunction(), CCInfo, Outs, /*IsRet=*/true,
10004  nullptr, CC_RISCV);
10005 
10006  if (CallConv == CallingConv::GHC && !RVLocs.empty())
10007  report_fatal_error("GHC functions return void only");
10008 
10009  SDValue Glue;
10010  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> RetOps(1, Chain);
10011 
10012  // Copy the result values into the output registers.
10013  for (unsigned i = 0, e = RVLocs.size(); i < e; ++i) {
10014  SDValue Val = OutVals[i];
10015  CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
10016  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
10017 
10018  if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64) {
10019  // Handle returning f64 on RV32D with a soft float ABI.
10020  assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Expected return via registers");
10021  SDValue SplitF64 = DAG.getNode(RISCVISD::SplitF64, DL,
10022  DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i32), Val);
10023  SDValue Lo = SplitF64.getValue(0);
10024  SDValue Hi = SplitF64.getValue(1);
10025  Register RegLo = VA.getLocReg();
10026  assert(RegLo < RISCV::X31 && "Invalid register pair");
10027  Register RegHi = RegLo + 1;
10028 
10029  if (STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(RegLo) ||
10030  STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(RegHi))
10031  MF.getFunction().getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
10032  MF.getFunction(),
10033  "Return value register required, but has been reserved."});
10034 
10035  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RegLo, Lo, Glue);
10036  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
10037  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegLo, MVT::i32));
10038  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RegHi, Hi, Glue);
10039  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
10040  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegHi, MVT::i32));
10041  } else {
10042  // Handle a 'normal' return.
10043  Val = convertValVTToLocVT(DAG, Val, VA, DL, Subtarget);
10044  Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), Val, Glue);
10045 
10046  if (STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(VA.getLocReg()))
10047  MF.getFunction().getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
10048  MF.getFunction(),
10049  "Return value register required, but has been reserved."});
10050 
10051  // Guarantee that all emitted copies are stuck together.
10052  Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
10053  RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
10054  }
10055  }
10056 
10057  RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
10058 
10059  // Add the glue node if we have it.
10060  if (Glue.getNode()) {
10061  RetOps.push_back(Glue);
10062  }
10063 
10064  unsigned RetOpc = RISCVISD::RET_FLAG;
10065  // Interrupt service routines use different return instructions.
10066  const Function &Func = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
10067  if (Func.hasFnAttribute("interrupt")) {
10068  if (!Func.getReturnType()->isVoidTy())
10069  report_fatal_error(
10070  "Functions with the interrupt attribute must have void return type!");
10071 
10072  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
10073  StringRef Kind =
10074  MF.getFunction().getFnAttribute("interrupt").getValueAsString();
10075 
10076  if (Kind == "user")
10077  RetOpc = RISCVISD::URET_FLAG;
10078  else if (Kind == "supervisor")
10079  RetOpc = RISCVISD::SRET_FLAG;
10080  else
10081  RetOpc = RISCVISD::MRET_FLAG;
10082  }
10083 
10084  return DAG.getNode(RetOpc, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
10085 }
10086 
10087 void RISCVTargetLowering::validateCCReservedRegs(
10088  const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<llvm::Register, llvm::SDValue>> &Regs,
10089  MachineFunction &MF) const {
10090  const Function &F = MF.getFunction();
10091  const RISCVSubtarget &STI = MF.getSubtarget<RISCVSubtarget>();
10092 
10093  if (llvm::any_of(Regs, [&STI](auto Reg) {
10094  return STI.isRegisterReservedByUser(Reg.first);
10095  }))
10096  F.getContext().diagnose(DiagnosticInfoUnsupported{
10097  F, "Argument register required, but has been reserved."});
10098 }
10099 
10100 bool RISCVTargetLowering::mayBeEmittedAsTailCall(const CallInst *CI) const {
10101  return CI->isTailCall();
10102 }

10257 
10258 /// getConstraintType - Given a constraint letter, return the type of
10259 /// constraint it is for this target.
10260 RISCVTargetLowering::ConstraintType
10261 RISCVTargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const {
10262  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
10263  switch (Constraint[0]) {
10264  default:
10265  break;
10266  case 'f':
10267  return C_RegisterClass;
10268  case 'I':
10269  case 'J':
10270  case 'K':
10271  return C_Immediate;
10272  case 'A':
10273  return C_Memory;
10274  case 'S': // A symbolic address
10275  return C_Other;
10276  }
10277  } else {
10278  if (Constraint == "vr" || Constraint == "vm")
10279  return C_RegisterClass;
10280  }
10281  return TargetLowering::getConstraintType(Constraint);
10282 }
10283 
10284 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *>
10285 RISCVTargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
10286  StringRef Constraint,
10287  MVT VT) const {
10288  // First, see if this is a constraint that directly corresponds to a
10289  // RISCV register class.
10290  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
10291  switch (Constraint[0]) {
10292  case 'r':
10293  // TODO: Support fixed vectors up to XLen for P extension?
10294  if (VT.isVector())
10295  break;
10296  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
10297  case 'f':
10298  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh() && VT == MVT::f16)
10299  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::FPR16RegClass);
10300  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF() && VT == MVT::f32)
10301  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::FPR32RegClass);
10302  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD() && VT == MVT::f64)
10303  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::FPR64RegClass);
10304  break;
10305  default:
10306  break;
10307  }
10308  } else if (Constraint == "vr") {
10309  for (const auto *RC : {&RISCV::VRRegClass, &RISCV::VRM2RegClass,
10310  &RISCV::VRM4RegClass, &RISCV::VRM8RegClass}) {
10311  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(*RC, VT.SimpleTy))
10312  return std::make_pair(0U, RC);
10313  }
10314  } else if (Constraint == "vm") {
10315  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(RISCV::VMV0RegClass, VT.SimpleTy))
10316  return std::make_pair(0U, &RISCV::VMV0RegClass);
10317  }
10318 
10319  // Clang will correctly decode the usage of register name aliases into their
10320  // official names. However, other frontends like `rustc` do not. This allows
10321  // users of these frontends to use the ABI names for registers in LLVM-style
10322  // register constraints.
10323  unsigned XRegFromAlias = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Constraint.lower())
10324  .Case("{zero}", RISCV::X0)
10325  .Case("{ra}", RISCV::X1)
10326  .Case("{sp}", RISCV::X2)
10327  .Case("{gp}", RISCV::X3)
10328  .Case("{tp}", RISCV::X4)
10329  .Case("{t0}", RISCV::X5)
10330  .Case("{t1}", RISCV::X6)
10331  .Case("{t2}", RISCV::X7)
10332  .Cases("{s0}", "{fp}", RISCV::X8)
10333  .Case("{s1}", RISCV::X9)
10334  .Case("{a0}", RISCV::X10)
10335  .Case("{a1}", RISCV::X11)
10336  .Case("{a2}", RISCV::X12)
10337  .Case("{a3}", RISCV::X13)
10338  .Case("{a4}", RISCV::X14)
10339  .Case("{a5}", RISCV::X15)
10340  .Case("{a6}", RISCV::X16)
10341  .Case("{a7}", RISCV::X17)
10342  .Case("{s2}", RISCV::X18)
10343  .Case("{s3}", RISCV::X19)
10344  .Case("{s4}", RISCV::X20)
10345  .Case("{s5}", RISCV::X21)
10346  .Case("{s6}", RISCV::X22)
10347  .Case("{s7}", RISCV::X23)
10348  .Case("{s8}", RISCV::X24)
10349  .Case("{s9}", RISCV::X25)
10350  .Case("{s10}", RISCV::X26)
10351  .Case("{s11}", RISCV::X27)
10352  .Case("{t3}", RISCV::X28)
10353  .Case("{t4}", RISCV::X29)
10354  .Case("{t5}", RISCV::X30)
10355  .Case("{t6}", RISCV::X31)
10356  .Default(RISCV::NoRegister);
10357  if (XRegFromAlias != RISCV::NoRegister)
10358  return std::make_pair(XRegFromAlias, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
10359 
10360  // Since TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint uses the name of the
10361  // TableGen record rather than the AsmName to choose registers for InlineAsm
10362  // constraints, plus we want to match those names to the widest floating point
10363  // register type available, manually select floating point registers here.
10364  //
10365  // The second case is the ABI name of the register, so that frontends can also
10366  // use the ABI names in register constraint lists.
10367  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtF()) {
10368  unsigned FReg = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Constraint.lower())
10369  .Cases("{f0}", "{ft0}", RISCV::F0_F)
10370  .Cases("{f1}", "{ft1}", RISCV::F1_F)
10371  .Cases("{f2}", "{ft2}", RISCV::F2_F)
10372  .Cases("{f3}", "{ft3}", RISCV::F3_F)
10373  .Cases("{f4}", "{ft4}", RISCV::F4_F)
10374  .Cases("{f5}", "{ft5}", RISCV::F5_F)
10375  .Cases("{f6}", "{ft6}", RISCV::F6_F)
10376  .Cases("{f7}", "{ft7}", RISCV::F7_F)
10377  .Cases("{f8}", "{fs0}", RISCV::F8_F)
10378  .Cases("{f9}", "{fs1}", RISCV::F9_F)
10379  .Cases("{f10}", "{fa0}", RISCV::F10_F)
10380  .Cases("{f11}", "{fa1}", RISCV::F11_F)
10381  .Cases("{f12}", "{fa2}", RISCV::F12_F)
10382  .Cases("{f13}", "{fa3}", RISCV::F13_F)
10383  .Cases("{f14}", "{fa4}", RISCV::F14_F)
10384  .Cases("{f15}", "{fa5}", RISCV::F15_F)
10385  .Cases("{f16}", "{fa6}", RISCV::F16_F)
10386  .Cases("{f17}", "{fa7}", RISCV::F17_F)
10387  .Cases("{f18}", "{fs2}", RISCV::F18_F)
10388  .Cases("{f19}", "{fs3}", RISCV::F19_F)
10389  .Cases("{f20}", "{fs4}", RISCV::F20_F)
10390  .Cases("{f21}", "{fs5}", RISCV::F21_F)
10391  .Cases("{f22}", "{fs6}", RISCV::F22_F)
10392  .Cases("{f23}", "{fs7}", RISCV::F23_F)
10393  .Cases("{f24}", "{fs8}", RISCV::F24_F)
10394  .Cases("{f25}", "{fs9}", RISCV::F25_F)
10395  .Cases("{f26}", "{fs10}", RISCV::F26_F)
10396  .Cases("{f27}", "{fs11}", RISCV::F27_F)
10397  .Cases("{f28}", "{ft8}", RISCV::F28_F)
10398  .Cases("{f29}", "{ft9}", RISCV::F29_F)
10399  .Cases("{f30}", "{ft10}", RISCV::F30_F)
10400  .Cases("{f31}", "{ft11}", RISCV::F31_F)
10401  .Default(RISCV::NoRegister);
10402  if (FReg != RISCV::NoRegister) {
10403  assert(RISCV::F0_F <= FReg && FReg <= RISCV::F31_F && "Unknown fp-reg");
10404  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtD() && (VT == MVT::f64 || VT == MVT::Other)) {
10405  unsigned RegNo = FReg - RISCV::F0_F;
10406  unsigned DReg = RISCV::F0_D + RegNo;
10407  return std::make_pair(DReg, &RISCV::FPR64RegClass);
10408  }
10409  if (VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::Other)
10410  return std::make_pair(FReg, &RISCV::FPR32RegClass);
10411  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZfh() && VT == MVT::f16) {
10412  unsigned RegNo = FReg - RISCV::F0_F;
10413  unsigned HReg = RISCV::F0_H + RegNo;
10414  return std::make_pair(HReg, &RISCV::FPR16RegClass);
10415  }
10416  }
10417  }
10418 
10419  if (Subtarget.hasVInstructions()) {
10420  Register VReg = StringSwitch<Register>(Constraint.lower())
10421  .Case("{v0}", RISCV::V0)
10422  .Case("{v1}", RISCV::V1)
10423  .Case("{v2}", RISCV::V2)
10424  .Case("{v3}", RISCV::V3)
10425  .Case("{v4}", RISCV::V4)
10426  .Case("{v5}", RISCV::V5)
10427  .Case("{v6}", RISCV::V6)
10428  .Case("{v7}", RISCV::V7)
10429  .Case("{v8}", RISCV::V8)
10430  .Case("{v9}", RISCV::V9)
10431  .Case("{v10}", RISCV::V10)
10432  .Case("{v11}", RISCV::V11)
10433  .Case("{v12}", RISCV::V12)
10434  .Case("{v13}", RISCV::V13)
10435  .Case("{v14}", RISCV::V14)
10436  .Case("{v15}", RISCV::V15)
10437  .Case("{v16}", RISCV::V16)
10438  .Case("{v17}", RISCV::V17)
10439  .Case("{v18}", RISCV::V18)
10440  .Case("{v19}", RISCV::V19)
10441  .Case("{v20}", RISCV::V20)
10442  .Case("{v21}", RISCV::V21)
10443  .Case("{v22}", RISCV::V22)
10444  .Case("{v23}", RISCV::V23)
10445  .Case("{v24}", RISCV::V24)
10446  .Case("{v25}", RISCV::V25)
10447  .Case("{v26}", RISCV::V26)
10448  .Case("{v27}", RISCV::V27)
10449  .Case("{v28}", RISCV::V28)
10450  .Case("{v29}", RISCV::V29)
10451  .Case("{v30}", RISCV::V30)
10452  .Case("{v31}", RISCV::V31)
10453  .Default(RISCV::NoRegister);
10454  if (VReg != RISCV::NoRegister) {
10455  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(RISCV::VMRegClass, VT.SimpleTy))
10456  return std::make_pair(VReg, &RISCV::VMRegClass);
10457  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(RISCV::VRRegClass, VT.SimpleTy))
10458  return std::make_pair(VReg, &RISCV::VRRegClass);
10459  for (const auto *RC :
10460  {&RISCV::VRM2RegClass, &RISCV::VRM4RegClass, &RISCV::VRM8RegClass}) {
10461  if (TRI->isTypeLegalForClass(*RC, VT.SimpleTy)) {
10462  VReg = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(VReg, RISCV::sub_vrm1_0, RC);
10463  return std::make_pair(VReg, RC);
10464  }
10465  }
10466  }
10467  }
10468 
10469  std::pair<Register, const TargetRegisterClass *> Res =
10470  TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
10471 
10472  // If we picked one of the Zfinx register classes, remap it to the GPR class.
10473  // FIXME: When Zfinx is supported in CodeGen this will need to take the
10474  // Subtarget into account.
10475  if (Res.second == &RISCV::GPRF16RegClass ||
10476  Res.second == &RISCV::GPRF32RegClass ||
10477  Res.second == &RISCV::GPRF64RegClass)
10478  return std::make_pair(Res.first, &RISCV::GPRRegClass);
10479 
10480  return Res;
10481 }
10482 
10483 unsigned
10484 RISCVTargetLowering::getInlineAsmMemConstraint(StringRef ConstraintCode) const {
10485  // Currently only support length 1 constraints.
10486  if (ConstraintCode.size() == 1) {
10487  switch (ConstraintCode[0]) {
10488  case 'A':
10489  return InlineAsm::Constraint_A;
10490  default:
10491  break;
10492  }
10493  }
10494 
10495  return TargetLowering::getInlineAsmMemConstraint(ConstraintCode);
10496 }
10497 
10498 void RISCVTargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(
10499  SDValue Op, std::string &Constraint, std::vector<SDValue> &Ops,
10500  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10501  // Currently only support length 1 constraints.
10502  if (Constraint.length() == 1) {
10503  switch (Constraint[0]) {
10504  case 'I':
10505  // Validate & create a 12-bit signed immediate operand.
10506  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
10507  uint64_t CVal = C->getSExtValue();
10508  if (isInt<12>(CVal))
10509  Ops.push_back(
10510  DAG.getTargetConstant(CVal, SDLoc(Op), Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
10511  }
10512  return;
10513  case 'J':
10514  // Validate & create an integer zero operand.
10515  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op))
10516  if (C->getZExtValue() == 0)
10517  Ops.push_back(
10518  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
10519  return;
10520  case 'K':
10521  // Validate & create a 5-bit unsigned immediate operand.
10522  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
10523  uint64_t CVal = C->getZExtValue();
10524  if (isUInt<5>(CVal))
10525  Ops.push_back(
10526  DAG.getTargetConstant(CVal, SDLoc(Op), Subtarget.getXLenVT()));
10527  }
10528  return;
10529  case 'S':
10530  if (const auto *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op)) {
10531  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), SDLoc(Op),
10532  GA->getValueType(0)));
10533  } else if (const auto *BA = dyn_cast<BlockAddressSDNode>(Op)) {
10534  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetBlockAddress(BA->getBlockAddress(),
10535  BA->getValueType(0)));
10536  }
10537  return;
10538  default:
10539  break;
10540  }
10541  }
10542  TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, Constraint, Ops, DAG);
10543 }
10544 
10545 Instruction *RISCVTargetLowering::emitLeadingFence(IRBuilderBase &Builder,
10546  Instruction *Inst,
10547  AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
10548  if (isa<LoadInst>(Inst) && Ord == AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent)
10549  return Builder.CreateFence(Ord);
10550  if (isa<StoreInst>(Inst) && isReleaseOrStronger(Ord))
10551  return Builder.CreateFence(AtomicOrdering::Release);
10552  return nullptr;
10553 }
10554 
10555 Instruction *RISCVTargetLowering::emitTrailingFence(IRBuilderBase &Builder,
10556  Instruction *Inst,
10557  AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
10558  if (isa<LoadInst>(Inst) && isAcquireOrStronger(Ord))
10559  return Builder.CreateFence(AtomicOrdering::Acquire);
10560  return nullptr;
10561 }
10562 
10563 TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind
10564 RISCVTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(AtomicRMWInst *AI) const {
10565  // atomicrmw {fadd,fsub} must be expanded to use compare-exchange, as floating
10566  // point operations can't be used in an lr/sc sequence without breaking the
10567  // forward-progress guarantee.
10568  if (AI->isFloatingPointOperation())
10569  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
10570 
10571  unsigned Size = AI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
10572  if (Size == 8 || Size == 16)
10573  return AtomicExpansionKind::MaskedIntrinsic;
10574  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
10575 }
10576 
10577 static Intrinsic::ID
10578 getIntrinsicForMaskedAtomicRMWBinOp(unsigned XLen, AtomicRMWInst::BinOp BinOp) {
10579  if (XLen == 32) {
10580  switch (BinOp) {
10581  default:
10582  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected AtomicRMW BinOp");
10583  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg:
10584  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_xchg_i32;
10585  case AtomicRMWInst::Add:
10586  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_add_i32;
10587  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub:
10588  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_sub_i32;
10589  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand:
10590  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_nand_i32;
10591  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
10592  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_max_i32;
10593  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
10594  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_min_i32;
10595  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax:
10596  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umax_i32;
10597  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
10598  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umin_i32;
10599  }
10600  }
10601 
10602  if (XLen == 64) {
10603  switch (BinOp) {
10604  default:
10605  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected AtomicRMW BinOp");
10606  case AtomicRMWInst::Xchg:
10607  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_xchg_i64;
10608  case AtomicRMWInst::Add:
10609  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_add_i64;
10610  case AtomicRMWInst::Sub:
10611  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_sub_i64;
10612  case AtomicRMWInst::Nand:
10613  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_nand_i64;
10614  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
10615  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_max_i64;
10616  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
10617  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_min_i64;
10618  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax:
10619  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umax_i64;
10620  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
10621  return Intrinsic::riscv_masked_atomicrmw_umin_i64;
10622  }
10623  }
10624 
10625  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected XLen\n");
10626 }
10627 
10628 Value *RISCVTargetLowering::emitMaskedAtomicRMWIntrinsic(
10629  IRBuilderBase &Builder, AtomicRMWInst *AI, Value *AlignedAddr, Value *Incr,
10630  Value *Mask, Value *ShiftAmt, AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
10631  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
10632  Value *Ordering =
10633  Builder.getIntN(XLen, static_cast<uint64_t>(AI->getOrdering()));
10634  Type *Tys[] = {AlignedAddr->getType()};
10635  Function *LrwOpScwLoop = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
10636  AI->getModule(),
10637  getIntrinsicForMaskedAtomicRMWBinOp(XLen, AI->getOperation()), Tys);
10638 
10639  if (XLen == 64) {
10640  Incr = Builder.CreateSExt(Incr, Builder.getInt64Ty());
10641  Mask = Builder.CreateSExt(Mask, Builder.getInt64Ty());
10642  ShiftAmt = Builder.CreateSExt(ShiftAmt, Builder.getInt64Ty());
10643  }
10644 
10645  Value *Result;
10646 
10647  // Must pass the shift amount needed to sign extend the loaded value prior
10648  // to performing a signed comparison for min/max. ShiftAmt is the number of
10649  // bits to shift the value into position. Pass XLen-ShiftAmt-ValWidth, which
10650  // is the number of bits to left+right shift the value in order to
10651  // sign-extend.
10652  if (AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::Min ||
10653  AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::Max) {
10654  const DataLayout &DL = AI->getModule()->getDataLayout();
10655  unsigned ValWidth =
10656  DL.getTypeStoreSizeInBits(AI->getValOperand()->getType());
10657  Value *SextShamt =
10658  Builder.CreateSub(Builder.getIntN(XLen, XLen - ValWidth), ShiftAmt);
10659  Result = Builder.CreateCall(LrwOpScwLoop,
10660  {AlignedAddr, Incr, Mask, SextShamt, Ordering});
10661  } else {
10662  Result =
10663  Builder.CreateCall(LrwOpScwLoop, {AlignedAddr, Incr, Mask, Ordering});
10664  }
10665 
10666  if (XLen == 64)
10667  Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt32Ty());
10668  return Result;
10669 }
10670 
10671 TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind
10672 RISCVTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicCmpXchgInIR(
10673  AtomicCmpXchgInst *CI) const {
10674  unsigned Size = CI->getCompareOperand()->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
10675  if (Size == 8 || Size == 16)
10676  return AtomicExpansionKind::MaskedIntrinsic;
10677  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
10678 }
10679 
10680 Value *RISCVTargetLowering::emitMaskedAtomicCmpXchgIntrinsic(
10681  IRBuilderBase &Builder, AtomicCmpXchgInst *CI, Value *AlignedAddr,
10682  Value *CmpVal, Value *NewVal, Value *Mask, AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
10683  unsigned XLen = Subtarget.getXLen();
10684  Value *Ordering = Builder.getIntN(XLen, static_cast<uint64_t>(Ord));
10685  Intrinsic::ID CmpXchgIntrID = Intrinsic::riscv_masked_cmpxchg_i32;
10686  if (XLen == 64) {
10687  CmpVal = Builder.CreateSExt(CmpVal, Builder.getInt64Ty());
10688  NewVal = Builder.CreateSExt(NewVal, Builder.getInt64Ty());
10689  Mask = Builder.CreateSExt(Mask, Builder.getInt64Ty());
10690  CmpXchgIntrID = Intrinsic::riscv_masked_cmpxchg_i64;
10691  }
10692  Type *Tys[] = {AlignedAddr->getType()};
10693  Function *MaskedCmpXchg =
10694  Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getModule(), CmpXchgIntrID, Tys);
10695  Value *Result = Builder.CreateCall(
10696  MaskedCmpXchg, {AlignedAddr, CmpVal, NewVal, Mask, Ordering});
10697  if (XLen == 64)
10698  Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt32Ty());
10699  return Result;
10700 }

10706 bool RISCVTargetLowering::shouldConvertFpToSat(unsigned Op, EVT FPVT,
10707  EVT VT) const {

10714  case MVT::f32:

10717  return Subtarget.hasStdExtD();
10718  default:
10719  return false;
10720  }
10721 }

10788 
10789 bool RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeMulByConstant(LLVMContext &Context, EVT VT,
10790  SDValue C) const {
10791  // Check integral scalar types.
10792  if (VT.isScalarInteger()) {
10793  // Omit the optimization if the sub target has the M extension and the data
10794  // size exceeds XLen.
10795  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtM() && VT.getSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getXLen())
10796  return false;
10797  if (auto *ConstNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(C.getNode())) {
10798  // Break the MUL to a SLLI and an ADD/SUB.
10799  const APInt &Imm = ConstNode->getAPIntValue();
10800  if ((Imm + 1).isPowerOf2() || (Imm - 1).isPowerOf2() ||
10801  (1 - Imm).isPowerOf2() || (-1 - Imm).isPowerOf2())
10802  return true;
10803  // Optimize the MUL to (SH*ADD x, (SLLI x, bits)) if Imm is not simm12.
10804  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtZba() && !Imm.isSignedIntN(12) &&
10805  ((Imm - 2).isPowerOf2() || (Imm - 4).isPowerOf2() ||
10806  (Imm - 8).isPowerOf2()))
10807  return true;
10808  // Omit the following optimization if the sub target has the M extension
10809  // and the data size >= XLen.
10810  if (Subtarget.hasStdExtM() && VT.getSizeInBits() >= Subtarget.getXLen())
10811  return false;
10812  // Break the MUL to two SLLI instructions and an ADD/SUB, if Imm needs
10813  // a pair of LUI/ADDI.
10814  if (!Imm.isSignedIntN(12) && Imm.countTrailingZeros() < 12) {
10815  APInt ImmS = Imm.ashr(Imm.countTrailingZeros());
10816  if ((ImmS + 1).isPowerOf2() || (ImmS - 1).isPowerOf2() ||
10817  (1 - ImmS).isPowerOf2())
10818  return true;
10819  }
10820  }
10821  }
10822 
10823  return false;
10824 }
10825 
10826 bool RISCVTargetLowering::isMulAddWithConstProfitable(
10827  const SDValue &AddNode, const SDValue &ConstNode) const {
10828  // Let the DAGCombiner decide for vectors.
10829  EVT VT = AddNode.getValueType();
10830  if (VT.isVector())
10831  return true;
10832 
10833  // Let the DAGCombiner decide for larger types.
10834  if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() > Subtarget.getXLen())
10835  return true;
10836 
10837  // It is worse if c1 is simm12 while c1*c2 is not.
10838  ConstantSDNode *C1Node = cast<ConstantSDNode>(AddNode.getOperand(1));
10839  ConstantSDNode *C2Node = cast<ConstantSDNode>(ConstNode);
10840  const APInt &C1 = C1Node->getAPIntValue();
10841  const APInt &C2 = C2Node->getAPIntValue();
10842  if (C1.isSignedIntN(12) && !(C1 * C2).isSignedIntN(12))
10843  return false;
10844 
10845  // Default to true and let the DAGCombiner decide.
10846  return true;
10847 }
10848 
10849 bool RISCVTargetLowering::allowsMisalignedMemoryAccesses(
10850  EVT VT, unsigned AddrSpace, Align Alignment, MachineMemOperand::Flags Flags,
10851  bool *Fast) const {
10852  if (!VT.isVector())
10853  return false;
10854 
10855  EVT ElemVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
10856  if (Alignment >= ElemVT.getStoreSize()) {
10857  if (Fast)
10858  *Fast = true;
10859  return true;
10860  }
10861 
10862  return false;
10863 }
10864 
10865 bool RISCVTargetLowering::splitValueIntoRegisterParts(
10866  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL, SDValue Val, SDValue *Parts,
10867  unsigned NumParts, MVT PartVT, Optional<CallingConv::ID> CC) const {
10868  bool IsABIRegCopy = CC.hasValue();
10869  EVT ValueVT = Val.getValueType();
10870  if (IsABIRegCopy && ValueVT == MVT::f16 && PartVT == MVT::f32) {
10871  // Cast the f16 to i16, extend to i32, pad with ones to make a float nan,
10872  // and cast to f32.
10873  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i16, Val);
10874  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, Val);
10875  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MVT::i32, Val,
10876  DAG.getConstant(0xFFFF0000, DL, MVT::i32));
10877  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f32, Val);
10878  Parts[0] = Val;
10879  return true;
10880  }
10881 
10882  if (ValueVT.isScalableVector() && PartVT.isScalableVector()) {
10883  LLVMContext &Context = *DAG.getContext();
10884  EVT ValueEltVT = ValueVT.getVectorElementType();
10885  EVT PartEltVT = PartVT.getVectorElementType();
10886  unsigned ValueVTBitSize = ValueVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
10887  unsigned PartVTBitSize = PartVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
10888  if (PartVTBitSize % ValueVTBitSize == 0) {
10889  assert(PartVTBitSize >= ValueVTBitSize);
10890  // If the element types are different, bitcast to the same element type of
10891  // PartVT first.
10892  // Give an example here, we want copy a <vscale x 1 x i8> value to
10893  // <vscale x 4 x i16>.
10894  // We need to convert <vscale x 1 x i8> to <vscale x 8 x i8> by insert
10895  // subvector, then we can bitcast to <vscale x 4 x i16>.
10896  if (ValueEltVT != PartEltVT) {
10897  if (PartVTBitSize > ValueVTBitSize) {
10898  unsigned Count = PartVTBitSize / ValueEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
10899  assert(Count != 0 && "The number of element should not be zero.");
10900  EVT SameEltTypeVT =
10901  EVT::getVectorVT(Context, ValueEltVT, Count, /*IsScalable=*/true);
10902  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, SameEltTypeVT,
10903  DAG.getUNDEF(SameEltTypeVT), Val,
10904  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
10905  }
10906  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, PartVT, Val);
10907  } else {
10908  Val =
10909  DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, PartVT, DAG.getUNDEF(PartVT),
10910  Val, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
10911  }
10912  Parts[0] = Val;
10913  return true;
10914  }
10915  }
10916  return false;
10917 }
10918 
10919 SDValue RISCVTargetLowering::joinRegisterPartsIntoValue(
10920  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL, const SDValue *Parts, unsigned NumParts,
10921  MVT PartVT, EVT ValueVT, Optional<CallingConv::ID> CC) const {
10922  bool IsABIRegCopy = CC.hasValue();
10923  if (IsABIRegCopy && ValueVT == MVT::f16 && PartVT == MVT::f32) {
10924  SDValue Val = Parts[0];
10925 
10926  // Cast the f32 to i32, truncate to i16, and cast back to f16.
10927  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Val);
10928  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i16, Val);
10929  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f16, Val);
10930  return Val;
10931  }
10932 
10933  if (ValueVT.isScalableVector() && PartVT.isScalableVector()) {
10934  LLVMContext &Context = *DAG.getContext();
10935  SDValue Val = Parts[0];
10936  EVT ValueEltVT = ValueVT.getVectorElementType();
10937  EVT PartEltVT = PartVT.getVectorElementType();
10938  unsigned ValueVTBitSize = ValueVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
10939  unsigned PartVTBitSize = PartVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
10940  if (PartVTBitSize % ValueVTBitSize == 0) {
10941  assert(PartVTBitSize >= ValueVTBitSize);
10942  EVT SameEltTypeVT = ValueVT;
10943  // If the element types are different, convert it to the same element type
10944  // of PartVT.
10945  // Give an example here, we want copy a <vscale x 1 x i8> value from
10946  // <vscale x 4 x i16>.
10947  // We need to convert <vscale x 4 x i16> to <vscale x 8 x i8> first,
10948  // then we can extract <vscale x 1 x i8>.
10949  if (ValueEltVT != PartEltVT) {
10950  unsigned Count = PartVTBitSize / ValueEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
10951  assert(Count != 0 && "The number of element should not be zero.");
10952  SameEltTypeVT =
10953  EVT::getVectorVT(Context, ValueEltVT, Count, /*IsScalable=*/true);
10954  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, SameEltTypeVT, Val);
10955  }
10956  Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, ValueVT, Val,
10957  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
10958  return Val;
10959  }
10960  }
10961  return SDValue();
10962 }
10963 
10964 SDValue
10965 RISCVTargetLowering::BuildSDIVPow2(SDNode *N, const APInt &Divisor,
10966  SelectionDAG &DAG,
10967  SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &Created) const {
10968  AttributeList Attr = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getAttributes();
10969  if (isIntDivCheap(N->getValueType(0), Attr))
10970  return SDValue(N, 0); // Lower SDIV as SDIV
10971 
10972  assert((Divisor.isPowerOf2() || Divisor.isNegatedPowerOf2()) &&
10973  "Unexpected divisor!");
10974 
10975  // Conditional move is needed, so do the transformation iff Zbt is enabled.
10976  if (!Subtarget.hasStdExtZbt())
10977  return SDValue();
10978 
10979  // When |Divisor| >= 2 ^ 12, it isn't profitable to do such transformation.
10980  // Besides, more critical path instructions will be generated when dividing
10981  // by 2. So we keep using the original DAGs for these cases.
10982  unsigned Lg2 = Divisor.countTrailingZeros();
10983  if (Lg2 == 1 || Lg2 >= 12)
10984  return SDValue();
10985 
10986  // fold (sdiv X, pow2)
10987  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10988  if (VT != MVT::i32 && !(Subtarget.is64Bit() && VT == MVT::i64))
10989  return SDValue();
10990 
10991  SDLoc DL(N);
10992  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
10993  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
10994  SDValue Pow2MinusOne = DAG.getConstant((1ULL << Lg2) - 1, DL, VT);
10995 
10996  // Add (N0 < 0) ? Pow2 - 1 : 0;
10997  SDValue Cmp = DAG.getSetCC(DL, VT, N0, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
10998  SDValue Add = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, N0, Pow2MinusOne);
10999  SDValue Sel = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DL, VT, Cmp, Add, N0);
11000 
11001  Created.push_back(Cmp.getNode());
11002  Created.push_back(Add.getNode());
11003  Created.push_back(Sel.getNode());
11004 
11005  // Divide by pow2.
11006  SDValue SRA =
11007  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Sel, DAG.getConstant(Lg2, DL, VT));
11008 
11009  // If we're dividing by a positive value, we're done. Otherwise, we must
11010  // negate the result.
11011  if (Divisor.isNonNegative())
11012  return SRA;
11013 
11014  Created.push_back(SRA.getNode());
11015  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), SRA);
11016 }
11017 
11018 #define GET_REGISTER_MATCHER
11019 #include "RISCVGenAsmMatcher.inc"
11020 
11021 Register
11022 RISCVTargetLowering::getRegisterByName(const char *RegName, LLT VT,
11023  const MachineFunction &MF) const {
11024  Register Reg = MatchRegisterAltName(RegName);
11025  if (Reg == RISCV::NoRegister)
11026  Reg = MatchRegisterName(RegName);
11027  if (Reg == RISCV::NoRegister)
11028  report_fatal_error(
11029  Twine("Invalid register name \"" + StringRef(RegName) + "\"."));
11030  BitVector ReservedRegs = Subtarget.getRegisterInfo()->getReservedRegs(MF);
11031  if (!ReservedRegs.test(Reg) && !Subtarget.isRegisterReservedByUser(Reg))
11032  report_fatal_error(Twine("Trying to obtain non-reserved register \"" +
11033  StringRef(RegName) + "\"."));
11034  return Reg;
11035 }
